161/// getGVAlignmentLog2 - Return the alignment to use for the specified global
162/// value in log2 form. This rounds up to the preferred alignment if possible
163/// and legal.
164static unsigned getGVAlignmentLog2(const GlobalValue *GV, const DataLayout &DL,
165 unsigned InBits = 0) {
166 unsigned NumBits = 0;
167 if (const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GV))
168 NumBits = DL.getPreferredAlignmentLog(GVar);
169
170 // If InBits is specified, round it to it.
171 if (InBits > NumBits)
172 NumBits = InBits;
173
174 // If the GV has a specified alignment, take it into account.
175 if (GV->getAlignment() == 0)
176 return NumBits;
177
178 unsigned GVAlign = Log2_32(GV->getAlignment());
179
180 // If the GVAlign is larger than NumBits, or if we are required to obey
181 // NumBits because the GV has an assigned section, obey it.
182 if (GVAlign > NumBits || GV->hasSection())
183 NumBits = GVAlign;
184 return NumBits;
185}

187AsmPrinter::AsmPrinter(TargetMachine &tm, std::unique_ptr<MCStreamer> Streamer)
188 : MachineFunctionPass(ID), TM(tm), MAI(tm.getMCAsmInfo()),
189 OutContext(Streamer->getContext()), OutStreamer(std::move(Streamer)) {
190 VerboseAsm = OutStreamer->isVerboseAsm();
191}
192
193AsmPrinter::~AsmPrinter() {
194 assert(!DD && Handlers.empty() && "Debug/EH info didn't get finalized");
195
196 if (GCMetadataPrinters) {
197 gcp_map_type &GCMap = getGCMap(GCMetadataPrinters);
198
199 delete &GCMap;
200 GCMetadataPrinters = nullptr;
201 }
202}

254
255bool AsmPrinter::doInitialization(Module &M) {
256 MMI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<MachineModuleInfo>();
257
258 // Initialize TargetLoweringObjectFile.
259 const_cast<TargetLoweringObjectFile&>(getObjFileLowering())
260 .Initialize(OutContext, TM);
261
262 const_cast<TargetLoweringObjectFile &>(getObjFileLowering())
263 .getModuleMetadata(M);
264
265 OutStreamer->InitSections(false);
266
267 // Emit the version-min deployment target directive if needed.
268 //
269 // FIXME: If we end up with a collection of these sorts of Darwin-specific
270 // or ELF-specific things, it may make sense to have a platform helper class
271 // that will work with the target helper class. For now keep it here, as the
272 // alternative is duplicated code in each of the target asm printers that
273 // use the directive, where it would need the same conditionalization
274 // anyway.
275 const Triple &Target = TM.getTargetTriple();
276 OutStreamer->EmitVersionForTarget(Target, M.getSDKVersion());
277
278 // Allow the target to emit any magic that it wants at the start of the file.
279 EmitStartOfAsmFile(M);
280
281 // Very minimal debug info. It is ignored if we emit actual debug info. If we
282 // don't, this at least helps the user find where a global came from.
283 if (MAI->hasSingleParameterDotFile()) {
284 // .file "foo.c"
285 OutStreamer->EmitFileDirective(
286 llvm::sys::path::filename(M.getSourceFileName()));
287 }
288
289 GCModuleInfo *MI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<GCModuleInfo>();
290 assert(MI && "AsmPrinter didn't require GCModuleInfo?");
291 for (auto &I : *MI)
292 if (GCMetadataPrinter *MP = GetOrCreateGCPrinter(*I))
293 MP->beginAssembly(M, *MI, *this);
294
295 // Emit module-level inline asm if it exists.
296 if (!M.getModuleInlineAsm().empty()) {
297 // We're at the module level. Construct MCSubtarget from the default CPU
298 // and target triple.
299 std::unique_ptr<MCSubtargetInfo> STI(TM.getTarget().createMCSubtargetInfo(
300 TM.getTargetTriple().str(), TM.getTargetCPU(),
301 TM.getTargetFeatureString()));
302 OutStreamer->AddComment("Start of file scope inline assembly");
303 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
304 EmitInlineAsm(M.getModuleInlineAsm()+"\n",
305 OutContext.getSubtargetCopy(*STI), TM.Options.MCOptions);
306 OutStreamer->AddComment("End of file scope inline assembly");
307 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
308 }
309
310 if (MAI->doesSupportDebugInformation()) {
311 bool EmitCodeView = MMI->getModule()->getCodeViewFlag();
312 if (EmitCodeView && TM.getTargetTriple().isOSWindows()) {
313 Handlers.emplace_back(llvm::make_unique<CodeViewDebug>(this),
314 DbgTimerName, DbgTimerDescription,
315 CodeViewLineTablesGroupName,
316 CodeViewLineTablesGroupDescription);
317 }
318 if (!EmitCodeView || MMI->getModule()->getDwarfVersion()) {
319 DD = new DwarfDebug(this, &M);
320 DD->beginModule();
321 Handlers.emplace_back(std::unique_ptr<DwarfDebug>(DD), DbgTimerName,
322 DbgTimerDescription, DWARFGroupName,
323 DWARFGroupDescription);
324 }
325 }
326
327 switch (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType()) {
328 case ExceptionHandling::SjLj:
329 case ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI:
330 case ExceptionHandling::ARM:
331 isCFIMoveForDebugging = true;
332 if (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() != ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI)
333 break;
334 for (auto &F: M.getFunctionList()) {
335 // If the module contains any function with unwind data,
336 // .eh_frame has to be emitted.
337 // Ignore functions that won't get emitted.
338 if (!F.isDeclarationForLinker() && F.needsUnwindTableEntry()) {
339 isCFIMoveForDebugging = false;
340 break;
341 }
342 }
343 break;
344 default:
345 isCFIMoveForDebugging = false;
346 break;
347 }
348
349 EHStreamer *ES = nullptr;
350 switch (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType()) {
351 case ExceptionHandling::None:
352 break;
353 case ExceptionHandling::SjLj:
354 case ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI:
355 ES = new DwarfCFIException(this);
356 break;
357 case ExceptionHandling::ARM:
358 ES = new ARMException(this);
359 break;
360 case ExceptionHandling::WinEH:
361 switch (MAI->getWinEHEncodingType()) {
362 default: llvm_unreachable("unsupported unwinding information encoding");
363 case WinEH::EncodingType::Invalid:
364 break;
365 case WinEH::EncodingType::X86:
366 case WinEH::EncodingType::Itanium:
367 ES = new WinException(this);
368 break;
369 }
370 break;
371 case ExceptionHandling::Wasm:
372 ES = new WasmException(this);
373 break;
374 }
375 if (ES)
376 Handlers.emplace_back(std::unique_ptr<EHStreamer>(ES), EHTimerName,
377 EHTimerDescription, DWARFGroupName,
378 DWARFGroupDescription);
379
380 if (mdconst::extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(
381 MMI->getModule()->getModuleFlag("cfguardtable")))
382 Handlers.emplace_back(llvm::make_unique<WinCFGuard>(this), CFGuardName,
383 CFGuardDescription, DWARFGroupName,
384 DWARFGroupDescription);
385
386 return false;
387}
388
389static bool canBeHidden(const GlobalValue *GV, const MCAsmInfo &MAI) {
390 if (!MAI.hasWeakDefCanBeHiddenDirective())
391 return false;
392
393 return GV->canBeOmittedFromSymbolTable();
394}
395
396void AsmPrinter::EmitLinkage(const GlobalValue *GV, MCSymbol *GVSym) const {
397 GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = GV->getLinkage();
398 switch (Linkage) {
399 case GlobalValue::CommonLinkage:
400 case GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage:
401 case GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage:
402 case GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage:
403 case GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage:
404 if (MAI->hasWeakDefDirective()) {
405 // .globl _foo
406 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Global);
407
408 if (!canBeHidden(GV, *MAI))
409 // .weak_definition _foo
410 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_WeakDefinition);
411 else
412 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_WeakDefAutoPrivate);
413 } else if (MAI->hasLinkOnceDirective()) {
414 // .globl _foo
415 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Global);
416 //NOTE: linkonce is handled by the section the symbol was assigned to.
417 } else {
418 // .weak _foo
419 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Weak);
420 }
421 return;
422 case GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage:
423 // If external, declare as a global symbol: .globl _foo
424 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Global);
425 return;
426 case GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage:
427 case GlobalValue::InternalLinkage:
428 return;
429 case GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage:
430 case GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage:
431 case GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage:
432 llvm_unreachable("Should never emit this");
433 }
434 llvm_unreachable("Unknown linkage type!");
435}

446/// EmitGlobalVariable - Emit the specified global variable to the .s file.
447void AsmPrinter::EmitGlobalVariable(const GlobalVariable *GV) {
448 bool IsEmuTLSVar = TM.useEmulatedTLS() && GV->isThreadLocal();
449 assert(!(IsEmuTLSVar && GV->hasCommonLinkage()) &&
450 "No emulated TLS variables in the common section");
451
452 // Never emit TLS variable xyz in emulated TLS model.
453 // The initialization value is in __emutls_t.xyz instead of xyz.
454 if (IsEmuTLSVar)
455 return;
456
457 if (GV->hasInitializer()) {
458 // Check to see if this is a special global used by LLVM, if so, emit it.
459 if (EmitSpecialLLVMGlobal(GV))
460 return;
461
462 // Skip the emission of global equivalents. The symbol can be emitted later
463 // on by emitGlobalGOTEquivs in case it turns out to be needed.
464 if (GlobalGOTEquivs.count(getSymbol(GV)))
465 return;
466
467 if (isVerbose()) {
468 // When printing the control variable __emutls_v.*,
469 // we don't need to print the original TLS variable name.
470 GV->printAsOperand(OutStreamer->GetCommentOS(),
471 /*PrintType=*/false, GV->getParent());
472 OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << '\n';
473 }
474 }
475
476 MCSymbol *GVSym = getSymbol(GV);
477 MCSymbol *EmittedSym = GVSym;
478
479 // getOrCreateEmuTLSControlSym only creates the symbol with name and default
480 // attributes.
481 // GV's or GVSym's attributes will be used for the EmittedSym.
482 EmitVisibility(EmittedSym, GV->getVisibility(), !GV->isDeclaration());
483
484 if (!GV->hasInitializer()) // External globals require no extra code.
485 return;
486
487 GVSym->redefineIfPossible();
488 if (GVSym->isDefined() || GVSym->isVariable())
489 report_fatal_error("symbol '" + Twine(GVSym->getName()) +
490 "' is already defined");
491
492 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
493 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(EmittedSym, MCSA_ELF_TypeObject);
494
495 SectionKind GVKind = TargetLoweringObjectFile::getKindForGlobal(GV, TM);
496
497 const DataLayout &DL = GV->getParent()->getDataLayout();
498 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GV->getType()->getElementType());
499
500 // If the alignment is specified, we *must* obey it. Overaligning a global
501 // with a specified alignment is a prompt way to break globals emitted to
502 // sections and expected to be contiguous (e.g. ObjC metadata).
503 unsigned AlignLog = getGVAlignmentLog2(GV, DL);
504
505 auto TS = OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer();
506 const TailPaddingAmount TailPadding =
507 TS ? TS->getTailPaddingForPreciseBounds(Size) : TailPaddingAmount::None;
508 const unsigned PreciseAlignment =
509 TS ? TS->getAlignmentForPreciseBounds(Size) : 1;
510
511 if (PreciseAlignment > (1u << AlignLog)) {
512 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nIncreased alignment for global from "
513 << (1u << AlignLog) << " to " << PreciseAlignment << ": ";
514 GV->dump(););
515 // Don't increase alignment if a custom section has been specified:
516 if (!GV->hasSection()) {
517 AlignLog = Log2_32(PreciseAlignment);
518 } else {
519 // TODO: add some attribute, emit a sensible warning?
520 errs() << "Not overriding global variable alignment for " << GV->getName()
521 << " since it has a section assigned.";
522 }
523 }
524
525 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
526 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription,
527 HI.TimerGroupName, HI.TimerGroupDescription,
528 TimePassesIsEnabled);
529 HI.Handler->setSymbolSize(GVSym, Size);
530 }
531
532 // Handle common symbols
533 if (GVKind.isCommon()) {
534 if (Size == 0) Size = 1; // .comm Foo, 0 is undefined, avoid it.
535 unsigned Align = 1 << AlignLog;
536 if (!getObjFileLowering().getCommDirectiveSupportsAlignment())
537 Align = 0;
538
539 // .comm _foo, 42, 4
540 OutStreamer->EmitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Align, TailPadding);
541 return;
542 }
543
544 // Determine to which section this global should be emitted.
545 MCSection *TheSection = getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(GV, GVKind, TM);
546
547 // If we have a bss global going to a section that supports the
548 // zerofill directive, do so here.
549 if (GVKind.isBSS() && MAI->hasMachoZeroFillDirective() &&
550 TheSection->isVirtualSection()) {
551 if (Size == 0)
552 Size = 1; // zerofill of 0 bytes is undefined.
553 unsigned Align = 1 << AlignLog;
554 EmitLinkage(GV, GVSym);
555 // .zerofill __DATA, __bss, _foo, 400, 5
556 OutStreamer->EmitZerofill(TheSection, GVSym, Size, Align, TailPadding);
557 return;
558 }
559
560 // If this is a BSS local symbol and we are emitting in the BSS
561 // section use .lcomm/.comm directive.
562 if (GVKind.isBSSLocal() &&
563 getObjFileLowering().getBSSSection() == TheSection) {
564 if (Size == 0)
565 Size = 1; // .comm Foo, 0 is undefined, avoid it.
566 unsigned Align = 1 << AlignLog;
567
568 // Use .lcomm only if it supports user-specified alignment.
569 // Otherwise, while it would still be correct to use .lcomm in some
570 // cases (e.g. when Align == 1), the external assembler might enfore
571 // some -unknown- default alignment behavior, which could cause
572 // spurious differences between external and integrated assembler.
573 // Prefer to simply fall back to .local / .comm in this case.
574 if (MAI->getLCOMMDirectiveAlignmentType() != LCOMM::NoAlignment) {
575 // .lcomm _foo, 42
576 OutStreamer->EmitLocalCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Align, TailPadding);
577 return;
578 }
579
580 if (!getObjFileLowering().getCommDirectiveSupportsAlignment())
581 Align = 0;
582
583 // .local _foo
584 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Local);
585 // .comm _foo, 42, 4
586 OutStreamer->EmitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Align, TailPadding);
587 return;
588 }
589
590 // Handle thread local data for mach-o which requires us to output an
591 // additional structure of data and mangle the original symbol so that we
592 // can reference it later.
593 //
594 // TODO: This should become an "emit thread local global" method on TLOF.
595 // All of this macho specific stuff should be sunk down into TLOFMachO and
596 // stuff like "TLSExtraDataSection" should no longer be part of the parent
597 // TLOF class. This will also make it more obvious that stuff like
598 // MCStreamer::EmitTBSSSymbol is macho specific and only called from macho
599 // specific code.
600 if (GVKind.isThreadLocal() && MAI->hasMachoTBSSDirective()) {
601 // Emit the .tbss symbol
602 MCSymbol *MangSym =
603 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(GVSym->getName() + Twine("$tlv$init"));
604
605 if (GVKind.isThreadBSS()) {
606 TheSection = getObjFileLowering().getTLSBSSSection();
607 OutStreamer->EmitTBSSSymbol(TheSection, MangSym, Size, TailPadding,
608 1 << AlignLog);
609 } else if (GVKind.isThreadData()) {
610 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(TheSection);
611
612 EmitAlignment(AlignLog, GV);
613 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(MangSym);
614
615 EmitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(),
616 static_cast<unsigned>(TailPadding));
617 }
618
619 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
620
621 // Emit the variable struct for the runtime.
622 MCSection *TLVSect = getObjFileLowering().getTLSExtraDataSection();
623
624 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(TLVSect);
625 // Emit the linkage here.
626 EmitLinkage(GV, GVSym);
627 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(GVSym);
628
629 // Three pointers in size:
630 // - __tlv_bootstrap - used to make sure support exists
631 // - spare pointer, used when mapped by the runtime
632 // - pointer to mangled symbol above with initializer
633 unsigned PtrSize = DL.getPointerTypeSize(GV->getType());
634 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(GetExternalSymbolSymbol("_tlv_bootstrap"),
635 PtrSize);
636 OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(0, PtrSize);
637 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(MangSym, PtrSize);
638
639 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
640 return;
641 }
642
643 MCSymbol *EmittedInitSym = GVSym;
644
645 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(TheSection);
646
647 EmitLinkage(GV, EmittedInitSym);
648 EmitAlignment(AlignLog, GV);
649
650 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(EmittedInitSym);
651
652 EmitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(),
653 static_cast<unsigned>(TailPadding));
654
655 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
656 // .size foo, 42
657 OutStreamer->emitELFSize(EmittedInitSym,
658 MCConstantExpr::create(Size, OutContext));
659
660 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
661}

663/// Emit the directive and value for debug thread local expression
664///
665/// \p Value - The value to emit.
666/// \p Size - The size of the integer (in bytes) to emit.
667void AsmPrinter::EmitDebugValue(const MCExpr *Value, unsigned Size) const {
668 OutStreamer->EmitValue(Value, Size);
669}

671/// EmitFunctionHeader - This method emits the header for the current
672/// function.
673void AsmPrinter::EmitFunctionHeader() {
674 const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
675
676 if (isVerbose())
677 OutStreamer->GetCommentOS()
678 << "-- Begin function "
679 << GlobalValue::dropLLVMManglingEscape(F.getName()) << '\n';
680
681 // Print out constants referenced by the function
682 EmitConstantPool();
683
684 // Print the 'header' of function.
685 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(&F, TM));
686 EmitVisibility(CurrentFnSym, F.getVisibility());
687
688 EmitLinkage(&F, CurrentFnSym);
689 if (MAI->hasFunctionAlignment())
690 EmitAlignment(MF->getAlignment(), &F);
691
692 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
693 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(CurrentFnSym, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction);
694
695 if (F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::Cold))
696 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(CurrentFnSym, MCSA_Cold);
697
698 if (isVerbose()) {
699 F.printAsOperand(OutStreamer->GetCommentOS(),
700 /*PrintType=*/false, F.getParent());
701 OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << '\n';
702 }
703
704 // Emit the prefix data.
705 if (F.hasPrefixData()) {
706 if (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols()) {
707 // Preserving prefix data on platforms which use subsections-via-symbols
708 // is a bit tricky. Here we introduce a symbol for the prefix data
709 // and use the .alt_entry attribute to mark the function's real entry point
710 // as an alternative entry point to the prefix-data symbol.
711 MCSymbol *PrefixSym = OutContext.createLinkerPrivateTempSymbol();
712 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(PrefixSym);
713
714 EmitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), F.getPrefixData(), 0);
715
716 // Emit an .alt_entry directive for the actual function symbol.
717 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(CurrentFnSym, MCSA_AltEntry);
718 } else {
719 EmitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), F.getPrefixData(), 0);
720 }
721 }
722
723 // Emit the CurrentFnSym. This is a virtual function to allow targets to
724 // do their wild and crazy things as required.
725 EmitFunctionEntryLabel();
726
727 // If the function had address-taken blocks that got deleted, then we have
728 // references to the dangling symbols. Emit them at the start of the function
729 // so that we don't get references to undefined symbols.
730 std::vector<MCSymbol*> DeadBlockSyms;
731 MMI->takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction(&F, DeadBlockSyms);
732 for (unsigned i = 0, e = DeadBlockSyms.size(); i != e; ++i) {
733 OutStreamer->AddComment("Address taken block that was later removed");
734 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(DeadBlockSyms[i]);
735 }
736
737 if (CurrentFnBegin) {
738 if (MAI->useAssignmentForEHBegin()) {
739 MCSymbol *CurPos = OutContext.createTempSymbol();
740 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(CurPos);
741 OutStreamer->EmitAssignment(CurrentFnBegin,
742 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurPos, OutContext));
743 } else {
744 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(CurrentFnBegin);
745 }
746 }
747
748 // Emit pre-function debug and/or EH information.
749 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
750 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
751 HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
752 HI.Handler->beginFunction(MF);
753 }
754
755 // Emit the prologue data.
756 if (F.hasPrologueData())
757 EmitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), F.getPrologueData(), 0);
758}
759
760/// EmitFunctionEntryLabel - Emit the label that is the entrypoint for the
761/// function. This can be overridden by targets as required to do custom stuff.
762void AsmPrinter::EmitFunctionEntryLabel() {
763 CurrentFnSym->redefineIfPossible();
764
765 // The function label could have already been emitted if two symbols end up
766 // conflicting due to asm renaming. Detect this and emit an error.
767 if (CurrentFnSym->isVariable())
768 report_fatal_error("'" + Twine(CurrentFnSym->getName()) +
769 "' is a protected alias");
770 if (CurrentFnSym->isDefined())
771 report_fatal_error("'" + Twine(CurrentFnSym->getName()) +
772 "' label emitted multiple times to assembly file");
773
774 return OutStreamer->EmitLabel(CurrentFnSym);
775}
776
777/// emitComments - Pretty-print comments for instructions.
778static void emitComments(const MachineInstr &MI, raw_ostream &CommentOS) {
779 const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getMF();
780 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
781
782 // Check for spills and reloads
783
784 // We assume a single instruction only has a spill or reload, not
785 // both.
786 Optional<unsigned> Size;
787 if ((Size = MI.getRestoreSize(TII))) {
788 CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Reload\n";
789 } else if ((Size = MI.getFoldedRestoreSize(TII))) {
790 if (*Size)
791 CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Folded Reload\n";
792 } else if ((Size = MI.getSpillSize(TII))) {
793 CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Spill\n";
794 } else if ((Size = MI.getFoldedSpillSize(TII))) {
795 if (*Size)
796 CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Folded Spill\n";
797 }
798
799 // Check for spill-induced copies
800 if (MI.getAsmPrinterFlag(MachineInstr::ReloadReuse))
801 CommentOS << " Reload Reuse\n";
802}

804/// emitImplicitDef - This method emits the specified machine instruction
805/// that is an implicit def.
806void AsmPrinter::emitImplicitDef(const MachineInstr *MI) const {
807 unsigned RegNo = MI->getOperand(0).getReg();
808
809 SmallString<128> Str;
810 raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
811 OS << "implicit-def: "
812 << printReg(RegNo, MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
813
814 OutStreamer->AddComment(OS.str());
815 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
816}
817
818static void emitKill(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
819 std::string Str;
820 raw_string_ostream OS(Str);
821 OS << "kill:";
822 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
823 const MachineOperand &Op = MI->getOperand(i);
824 assert(Op.isReg() && "KILL instruction must have only register operands");
825 OS << ' ' << (Op.isDef() ? "def " : "killed ")
826 << printReg(Op.getReg(), AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
827 }
828 AP.OutStreamer->AddComment(OS.str());
829 AP.OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
830}
831
832/// emitDebugValueComment - This method handles the target-independent form
833/// of DBG_VALUE, returning true if it was able to do so. A false return
834/// means the target will need to handle MI in EmitInstruction.
835static bool emitDebugValueComment(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
836 // This code handles only the 4-operand target-independent form.
837 if (MI->getNumOperands() != 4)
838 return false;
839
840 SmallString<128> Str;
841 raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
842 OS << "DEBUG_VALUE: ";
843
844 const DILocalVariable *V = MI->getDebugVariable();
845 if (auto *SP = dyn_cast<DISubprogram>(V->getScope())) {
846 StringRef Name = SP->getName();
847 if (!Name.empty())
848 OS << Name << ":";
849 }
850 OS << V->getName();
851 OS << " <- ";
852
853 // The second operand is only an offset if it's an immediate.
854 bool MemLoc = MI->getOperand(0).isReg() && MI->getOperand(1).isImm();
855 int64_t Offset = MemLoc ? MI->getOperand(1).getImm() : 0;
856 const DIExpression *Expr = MI->getDebugExpression();
857 if (Expr->getNumElements()) {
858 OS << '[';
859 bool NeedSep = false;
860 for (auto Op : Expr->expr_ops()) {
861 if (NeedSep)
862 OS << ", ";
863 else
864 NeedSep = true;
865 OS << dwarf::OperationEncodingString(Op.getOp());
866 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Op.getNumArgs(); ++I)
867 OS << ' ' << Op.getArg(I);
868 }
869 OS << "] ";
870 }
871
872 // Register or immediate value. Register 0 means undef.
873 if (MI->getOperand(0).isFPImm()) {
874 APFloat APF = APFloat(MI->getOperand(0).getFPImm()->getValueAPF());
875 if (MI->getOperand(0).getFPImm()->getType()->isFloatTy()) {
876 OS << (double)APF.convertToFloat();
877 } else if (MI->getOperand(0).getFPImm()->getType()->isDoubleTy()) {
878 OS << APF.convertToDouble();
879 } else {
880 // There is no good way to print long double. Convert a copy to
881 // double. Ah well, it's only a comment.
882 bool ignored;
883 APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
884 &ignored);
885 OS << "(long double) " << APF.convertToDouble();
886 }
887 } else if (MI->getOperand(0).isImm()) {
888 OS << MI->getOperand(0).getImm();
889 } else if (MI->getOperand(0).isCImm()) {
890 MI->getOperand(0).getCImm()->getValue().print(OS, false /*isSigned*/);
891 } else {
892 unsigned Reg;
893 if (MI->getOperand(0).isReg()) {
894 Reg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg();
895 } else {
896 assert(MI->getOperand(0).isFI() && "Unknown operand type");
897 const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = AP.MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering();
898 Offset += TFI->getFrameIndexReference(*AP.MF,
899 MI->getOperand(0).getIndex(), Reg);
900 MemLoc = true;
901 }
902 if (Reg == 0) {
903 // Suppress offset, it is not meaningful here.
904 OS << "undef";
905 // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
906 AP.OutStreamer->emitRawComment(OS.str());
907 return true;
908 }
909 if (MemLoc)
910 OS << '[';
911 OS << printReg(Reg, AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
912 }
913
914 if (MemLoc)
915 OS << '+' << Offset << ']';
916
917 // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
918 AP.OutStreamer->emitRawComment(OS.str());
919 return true;
920}

922/// This method handles the target-independent form of DBG_LABEL, returning
923/// true if it was able to do so. A false return means the target will need
924/// to handle MI in EmitInstruction.
925static bool emitDebugLabelComment(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
926 if (MI->getNumOperands() != 1)
927 return false;
928
929 SmallString<128> Str;
930 raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
931 OS << "DEBUG_LABEL: ";
932
933 const DILabel *V = MI->getDebugLabel();
934 if (auto *SP = dyn_cast<DISubprogram>(V->getScope())) {
935 StringRef Name = SP->getName();
936 if (!Name.empty())
937 OS << Name << ":";
938 }
939 OS << V->getName();
940
941 // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
942 AP.OutStreamer->emitRawComment(OS.str());
943 return true;
944}

946AsmPrinter::CFIMoveType AsmPrinter::needsCFIMoves() const {
947 if (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI &&
948 MF->getFunction().needsUnwindTableEntry())
949 return CFI_M_EH;
950
951 if (MMI->hasDebugInfo())
952 return CFI_M_Debug;
953
954 return CFI_M_None;
955}
956
957bool AsmPrinter::needsSEHMoves() {
958 return MAI->usesWindowsCFI() && MF->getFunction().needsUnwindTableEntry();
959}
960
961void AsmPrinter::emitCFIInstruction(const MachineInstr &MI) {
962 ExceptionHandling ExceptionHandlingType = MAI->getExceptionHandlingType();
963 if (ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI &&
964 ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::ARM)
965 return;
966
967 if (needsCFIMoves() == CFI_M_None)
968 return;
969
970 // If there is no "real" instruction following this CFI instruction, skip
971 // emitting it; it would be beyond the end of the function's FDE range.
972 auto *MBB = MI.getParent();
973 auto I = std::next(MI.getIterator());
974 while (I != MBB->end() && I->isTransient())
975 ++I;
976 if (I == MBB->instr_end() &&
977 MBB->getReverseIterator() == MBB->getParent()->rbegin())
978 return;
979
980 const std::vector<MCCFIInstruction> &Instrs = MF->getFrameInstructions();
981 unsigned CFIIndex = MI.getOperand(0).getCFIIndex();
982 const MCCFIInstruction &CFI = Instrs[CFIIndex];
983 emitCFIInstruction(CFI);
984}
985
986void AsmPrinter::emitFrameAlloc(const MachineInstr &MI) {
987 // The operands are the MCSymbol and the frame offset of the allocation.
988 MCSymbol *FrameAllocSym = MI.getOperand(0).getMCSymbol();
989 int FrameOffset = MI.getOperand(1).getImm();
990
991 // Emit a symbol assignment.
992 OutStreamer->EmitAssignment(FrameAllocSym,
993 MCConstantExpr::create(FrameOffset, OutContext));
994}
995
996void AsmPrinter::emitStackSizeSection(const MachineFunction &MF) {
997 if (!MF.getTarget().Options.EmitStackSizeSection)
998 return;
999
1000 MCSection *StackSizeSection =
1001 getObjFileLowering().getStackSizesSection(*getCurrentSection());
1002 if (!StackSizeSection)
1003 return;
1004
1005 const MachineFrameInfo &FrameInfo = MF.getFrameInfo();
1006 // Don't emit functions with dynamic stack allocations.
1007 if (FrameInfo.hasVarSizedObjects())
1008 return;
1009
1010 OutStreamer->PushSection();
1011 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(StackSizeSection);
1012
1013 const MCSymbol *FunctionSymbol = getFunctionBegin();
1014 uint64_t StackSize = FrameInfo.getStackSize();
1015 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(FunctionSymbol, TM.getProgramPointerSize());
1016 OutStreamer->EmitULEB128IntValue(StackSize);
1017
1018 OutStreamer->PopSection();
1019}

1021static bool needFuncLabelsForEHOrDebugInfo(const MachineFunction &MF,
1022 MachineModuleInfo *MMI) {
1023 if (!MF.getLandingPads().empty() || MF.hasEHFunclets() || MMI->hasDebugInfo())
1024 return true;
1025
1026 // We might emit an EH table that uses function begin and end labels even if
1027 // we don't have any landingpads.
1028 if (!MF.getFunction().hasPersonalityFn())
1029 return false;
1030 return !isNoOpWithoutInvoke(
1031 classifyEHPersonality(MF.getFunction().getPersonalityFn()));
1032}
1033
1034/// EmitFunctionBody - This method emits the body and trailer for a
1035/// function.
1036void AsmPrinter::EmitFunctionBody() {
1037 EmitFunctionHeader();
1038
1039 // Emit target-specific gunk before the function body.
1040 EmitFunctionBodyStart();
1041
1042 bool ShouldPrintDebugScopes = MMI->hasDebugInfo();
1043
1044 if (isVerbose()) {
1045 // Get MachineDominatorTree or compute it on the fly if it's unavailable
1046 MDT = getAnalysisIfAvailable<MachineDominatorTree>();
1047 if (!MDT) {
1048 OwnedMDT = make_unique<MachineDominatorTree>();
1049 OwnedMDT->getBase().recalculate(*MF);
1050 MDT = OwnedMDT.get();
1051 }
1052
1053 // Get MachineLoopInfo or compute it on the fly if it's unavailable
1054 MLI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<MachineLoopInfo>();
1055 if (!MLI) {
1056 OwnedMLI = make_unique<MachineLoopInfo>();
1057 OwnedMLI->getBase().analyze(MDT->getBase());
1058 MLI = OwnedMLI.get();
1059 }
1060 }
1061
1062 // Print out code for the function.
1063 bool HasAnyRealCode = false;
1064 int NumInstsInFunction = 0;
1065 for (auto &MBB : *MF) {
1066 // Print a label for the basic block.
1067 EmitBasicBlockStart(MBB);
1068 for (auto &MI : MBB) {
1069 // Print the assembly for the instruction.
1070 if (!MI.isPosition() && !MI.isImplicitDef() && !MI.isKill() &&
1071 !MI.isDebugInstr()) {
1072 HasAnyRealCode = true;
1073 ++NumInstsInFunction;
1074 }
1075
1076 // If there is a pre-instruction symbol, emit a label for it here.
1077 if (MCSymbol *S = MI.getPreInstrSymbol())
1078 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(S);
1079
1080 if (ShouldPrintDebugScopes) {
1081 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1082 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription,
1083 HI.TimerGroupName, HI.TimerGroupDescription,
1084 TimePassesIsEnabled);
1085 HI.Handler->beginInstruction(&MI);
1086 }
1087 }
1088
1089 if (isVerbose())
1090 emitComments(MI, OutStreamer->GetCommentOS());
1091
1092 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1093 case TargetOpcode::CFI_INSTRUCTION:
1094 emitCFIInstruction(MI);
1095 break;
1096 case TargetOpcode::LOCAL_ESCAPE:
1097 emitFrameAlloc(MI);
1098 break;
1099 case TargetOpcode::ANNOTATION_LABEL:
1100 case TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL:
1101 case TargetOpcode::GC_LABEL:
1102 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(MI.getOperand(0).getMCSymbol());
1103 break;
1104 case TargetOpcode::INLINEASM:
1105 case TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR:
1106 EmitInlineAsm(&MI);
1107 break;
1108 case TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE:
1109 if (isVerbose()) {
1110 if (!emitDebugValueComment(&MI, *this))
1111 EmitInstruction(&MI);
1112 }
1113 break;
1114 case TargetOpcode::DBG_LABEL:
1115 if (isVerbose()) {
1116 if (!emitDebugLabelComment(&MI, *this))
1117 EmitInstruction(&MI);
1118 }
1119 break;
1120 case TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF:
1121 if (isVerbose()) emitImplicitDef(&MI);
1122 break;
1123 case TargetOpcode::KILL:
1124 if (isVerbose()) emitKill(&MI, *this);
1125 break;
1126 default:
1127 EmitInstruction(&MI);
1128 break;
1129 }
1130
1131 // If there is a post-instruction symbol, emit a label for it here.
1132 if (MCSymbol *S = MI.getPostInstrSymbol())
1133 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(S);
1134
1135 if (ShouldPrintDebugScopes) {
1136 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1137 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription,
1138 HI.TimerGroupName, HI.TimerGroupDescription,
1139 TimePassesIsEnabled);
1140 HI.Handler->endInstruction();
1141 }
1142 }
1143 }
1144
1145 EmitBasicBlockEnd(MBB);
1146 }
1147
1148 EmittedInsts += NumInstsInFunction;
1149 MachineOptimizationRemarkAnalysis R(DEBUG_TYPE, "InstructionCount",
1150 MF->getFunction().getSubprogram(),
1151 &MF->front());
1152 R << ore::NV("NumInstructions", NumInstsInFunction)
1153 << " instructions in function";
1154 ORE->emit(R);
1155
1156 // If the function is empty and the object file uses .subsections_via_symbols,
1157 // then we need to emit *something* to the function body to prevent the
1158 // labels from collapsing together. Just emit a noop.
1159 // Similarly, don't emit empty functions on Windows either. It can lead to
1160 // duplicate entries (two functions with the same RVA) in the Guard CF Table
1161 // after linking, causing the kernel not to load the binary:
1162 // https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/45366/vc-linker-creates-invalid-dll-with-clang-cl.html
1163 // FIXME: Hide this behind some API in e.g. MCAsmInfo or MCTargetStreamer.
1164 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple();
1165 if (!HasAnyRealCode && (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols() ||
1166 (TT.isOSWindows() && TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF()))) {
1167 MCInst Noop;
1168 MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()->getNoop(Noop);
1169
1170 // Targets can opt-out of emitting the noop here by leaving the opcode
1171 // unspecified.
1172 if (Noop.getOpcode()) {
1173 OutStreamer->AddComment("avoids zero-length function");
1174 OutStreamer->EmitInstruction(Noop, getSubtargetInfo());
1175 }
1176 }
1177
1178 const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
1179 for (const auto &BB : F) {
1180 if (!BB.hasAddressTaken())
1181 continue;
1182 MCSymbol *Sym = GetBlockAddressSymbol(&BB);
1183 if (Sym->isDefined())
1184 continue;
1185 OutStreamer->AddComment("Address of block that was removed by CodeGen");
1186 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(Sym);
1187 }
1188
1189 // Emit target-specific gunk after the function body.
1190 EmitFunctionBodyEnd();
1191
1192 if (needFuncLabelsForEHOrDebugInfo(*MF, MMI) ||
1193 MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective()) {
1194 // Create a symbol for the end of function.
1195 CurrentFnEnd = createTempSymbol("func_end");
1196 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(CurrentFnEnd);
1197 }
1198
1199 // If the target wants a .size directive for the size of the function, emit
1200 // it.
1201 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective()) {
1202 // We can get the size as difference between the function label and the
1203 // temp label.
1204 const MCExpr *SizeExp = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
1205 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnEnd, OutContext),
1206 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnSymForSize, OutContext), OutContext);
1207 OutStreamer->emitELFSize(CurrentFnSym, SizeExp);
1208 }
1209
1210 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1211 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1212 HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1213 HI.Handler->markFunctionEnd();
1214 }
1215
1216 // Print out jump tables referenced by the function.
1217 EmitJumpTableInfo();
1218
1219 // Emit post-function debug and/or EH information.
1220 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1221 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1222 HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1223 HI.Handler->endFunction(MF);
1224 }
1225
1226 // Emit section containing stack size metadata.
1227 emitStackSizeSection(*MF);
1228
1229 if (isVerbose())
1230 OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << "-- End function\n";
1231
1232 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
1233}
1234
1235/// Compute the number of Global Variables that uses a Constant.
1236static unsigned getNumGlobalVariableUses(const Constant *C) {
1237 if (!C)
1238 return 0;
1239
1240 if (isa<GlobalVariable>(C))
1241 return 1;
1242
1243 unsigned NumUses = 0;
1244 for (auto *CU : C->users())
1245 NumUses += getNumGlobalVariableUses(dyn_cast<Constant>(CU));
1246
1247 return NumUses;
1248}
1249
1250/// Only consider global GOT equivalents if at least one user is a
1251/// cstexpr inside an initializer of another global variables. Also, don't
1252/// handle cstexpr inside instructions. During global variable emission,
1253/// candidates are skipped and are emitted later in case at least one cstexpr
1254/// isn't replaced by a PC relative GOT entry access.
1255static bool isGOTEquivalentCandidate(const GlobalVariable *GV,
1256 unsigned &NumGOTEquivUsers) {
1257 // Global GOT equivalents are unnamed private globals with a constant
1258 // pointer initializer to another global symbol. They must point to a
1259 // GlobalVariable or Function, i.e., as GlobalValue.
1260 if (!GV->hasGlobalUnnamedAddr() || !GV->hasInitializer() ||
1261 !GV->isConstant() || !GV->isDiscardableIfUnused() ||
1262 !isa<GlobalValue>(GV->getOperand(0)))
1263 return false;
1264
1265 // To be a got equivalent, at least one of its users need to be a constant
1266 // expression used by another global variable.
1267 for (auto *U : GV->users())
1268 NumGOTEquivUsers += getNumGlobalVariableUses(dyn_cast<Constant>(U));
1269
1270 return NumGOTEquivUsers > 0;
1271}
1272
1273/// Unnamed constant global variables solely contaning a pointer to
1274/// another globals variable is equivalent to a GOT table entry; it contains the
1275/// the address of another symbol. Optimize it and replace accesses to these
1276/// "GOT equivalents" by using the GOT entry for the final global instead.
1277/// Compute GOT equivalent candidates among all global variables to avoid
1278/// emitting them if possible later on, after it use is replaced by a GOT entry
1279/// access.
1280void AsmPrinter::computeGlobalGOTEquivs(Module &M) {
1281 if (!getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel())
1282 return;
1283
1284 for (const auto &G : M.globals()) {
1285 unsigned NumGOTEquivUsers = 0;
1286 if (!isGOTEquivalentCandidate(&G, NumGOTEquivUsers))
1287 continue;
1288
1289 const MCSymbol *GOTEquivSym = getSymbol(&G);
1290 GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym] = std::make_pair(&G, NumGOTEquivUsers);
1291 }
1292}
1293
1294/// Constant expressions using GOT equivalent globals may not be eligible
1295/// for PC relative GOT entry conversion, in such cases we need to emit such
1296/// globals we previously omitted in EmitGlobalVariable.
1297void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalGOTEquivs() {
1298 if (!getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel())
1299 return;
1300
1301 SmallVector<const GlobalVariable *, 8> FailedCandidates;
1302 for (auto &I : GlobalGOTEquivs) {
1303 const GlobalVariable *GV = I.second.first;
1304 unsigned Cnt = I.second.second;
1305 if (Cnt)
1306 FailedCandidates.push_back(GV);
1307 }
1308 GlobalGOTEquivs.clear();
1309
1310 for (auto *GV : FailedCandidates)
1311 EmitGlobalVariable(GV);
1312}
1313
1314void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalIndirectSymbol(Module &M,
1315 const GlobalIndirectSymbol& GIS) {
1316 MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&GIS);
1317
1318 if (GIS.hasExternalLinkage() || !MAI->getWeakRefDirective())
1319 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_Global);
1320 else if (GIS.hasWeakLinkage() || GIS.hasLinkOnceLinkage())
1321 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_WeakReference);
1322 else
1323 assert(GIS.hasLocalLinkage() && "Invalid alias or ifunc linkage");
1324
1325 bool IsFunction = GIS.getType()->getPointerElementType()->isFunctionTy();
1326
1327 // Treat bitcasts of functions as functions also. This is important at least
1328 // on WebAssembly where object and function addresses can't alias each other.
1329 if (!IsFunction)
1330 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(GIS.getIndirectSymbol()))
1331 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::BitCast)
1332 IsFunction =
1333 CE->getOperand(0)->getType()->getPointerElementType()->isFunctionTy();
1334
1335 // Set the symbol type to function if the alias has a function type.
1336 // This affects codegen when the aliasee is not a function.
1337 if (IsFunction) {
1338 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction);
1339 if (isa<GlobalIFunc>(GIS))
1340 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_ELF_TypeIndFunction);
1341 }
1342
1343 EmitVisibility(Name, GIS.getVisibility());
1344
1345 const MCExpr *Expr = lowerConstant(GIS.getIndirectSymbol());
1346
1347 if (isa<GlobalAlias>(&GIS) && MAI->hasAltEntry() && isa<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr))
1348 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_AltEntry);
1349
1350 // Emit the directives as assignments aka .set:
1351 OutStreamer->EmitAssignment(Name, Expr);
1352
1353 if (auto *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(&GIS)) {
1354 // If the aliasee does not correspond to a symbol in the output, i.e. the
1355 // alias is not of an object or the aliased object is private, then set the
1356 // size of the alias symbol from the type of the alias. We don't do this in
1357 // other situations as the alias and aliasee having differing types but same
1358 // size may be intentional.
1359 const GlobalObject *BaseObject = GA->getBaseObject();
1360 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective() && GA->getValueType()->isSized() &&
1361 (!BaseObject || BaseObject->hasPrivateLinkage())) {
1362 const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
1363 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GA->getValueType());
1364 OutStreamer->emitELFSize(Name, MCConstantExpr::create(Size, OutContext));
1365 }
1366 }
1367}
1368
1369void AsmPrinter::emitRemarksSection(Module &M) {
1370 RemarkStreamer *RS = M.getContext().getRemarkStreamer();
1371 if (!RS)
1372 return;
1373 const remarks::Serializer &Serializer = RS->getSerializer();
1374
1375 // Switch to the right section: .remarks/__remarks.
1376 MCSection *RemarksSection =
1377 OutContext.getObjectFileInfo()->getRemarksSection();
1378 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(RemarksSection);
1379
1380 // Emit the magic number.
1381 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(remarks::Magic);
1382 // Explicitly emit a '\0'.
1383 OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(/*Value=*/0, /*Size=*/1);
1384
1385 // Emit the version number: little-endian uint64_t.
1386 // The version number is located at the offset 0x0 in the section.
1387 std::array<char, 8> Version;
1388 support::endian::write64le(Version.data(), remarks::Version);
1389 OutStreamer->EmitBinaryData(StringRef(Version.data(), Version.size()));
1390
1391 // Emit the string table in the section.
1392 // Note: we need to use the streamer here to emit it in the section. We can't
1393 // just use the serialize function with a raw_ostream because of the way
1394 // MCStreamers work.
1395 uint64_t StrTabSize =
1396 Serializer.StrTab ? Serializer.StrTab->SerializedSize : 0;
1397 // Emit the total size of the string table (the size itself excluded):
1398 // little-endian uint64_t.
1399 // The total size is located after the version number.
1400 // Note: even if no string table is used, emit 0.
1401 std::array<char, 8> StrTabSizeBuf;
1402 support::endian::write64le(StrTabSizeBuf.data(), StrTabSize);
1403 OutStreamer->EmitBinaryData(
1404 StringRef(StrTabSizeBuf.data(), StrTabSizeBuf.size()));
1405
1406 if (const Optional<remarks::StringTable> &StrTab = Serializer.StrTab) {
1407 std::vector<StringRef> StrTabStrings = StrTab->serialize();
1408 // Emit a list of null-terminated strings.
1409 // Note: the order is important here: the ID used in the remarks corresponds
1410 // to the position of the string in the section.
1411 for (StringRef Str : StrTabStrings) {
1412 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(Str);
1413 // Explicitly emit a '\0'.
1414 OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(/*Value=*/0, /*Size=*/1);
1415 }
1416 }
1417
1418 // Emit the null-terminated absolute path to the remark file.
1419 // The path is located at the offset 0x4 in the section.
1420 StringRef FilenameRef = RS->getFilename();
1421 SmallString<128> Filename = FilenameRef;
1422 sys::fs::make_absolute(Filename);
1423 assert(!Filename.empty() && "The filename can't be empty.");
1424 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(Filename);
1425 // Explicitly emit a '\0'.
1426 OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(/*Value=*/0, /*Size=*/1);
1427}
1428
1429bool AsmPrinter::doFinalization(Module &M) {
1430 // Set the MachineFunction to nullptr so that we can catch attempted
1431 // accesses to MF specific features at the module level and so that
1432 // we can conditionalize accesses based on whether or not it is nullptr.
1433 MF = nullptr;
1434
1435 // Gather all GOT equivalent globals in the module. We really need two
1436 // passes over the globals: one to compute and another to avoid its emission
1437 // in EmitGlobalVariable, otherwise we would not be able to handle cases
1438 // where the got equivalent shows up before its use.
1439 computeGlobalGOTEquivs(M);
1440
1441 // Emit global variables.
1442 for (const auto &G : M.globals())
1443 EmitGlobalVariable(&G);
1444
1445 // Emit remaining GOT equivalent globals.
1446 emitGlobalGOTEquivs();
1447
1448 // Emit visibility info for declarations
1449 for (const Function &F : M) {
1450 if (!F.isDeclarationForLinker())
1451 continue;
1452 GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes V = F.getVisibility();
1453 if (V == GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility)
1454 continue;
1455
1456 MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&F);
1457 EmitVisibility(Name, V, false);
1458 }
1459
1460 // Emit the remarks section contents.
1461 // FIXME: Figure out when is the safest time to emit this section. It should
1462 // not come after debug info.
1463 if (EnableRemarksSection)
1464 emitRemarksSection(M);
1465
1466 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = getObjFileLowering();
1467
1468 TLOF.emitModuleMetadata(*OutStreamer, M);
1469
1470 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
1471 MachineModuleInfoELF &MMIELF = MMI->getObjFileInfo<MachineModuleInfoELF>();
1472
1473 // Output stubs for external and common global variables.
1474 MachineModuleInfoELF::SymbolListTy Stubs = MMIELF.GetGVStubList();
1475 if (!Stubs.empty()) {
1476 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(TLOF.getDataSection());
1477 const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
1478 unsigned AS = DL.getProgramAddressSpace();
1479 unsigned Size = DL.getPointerSize(AS);
1480
1481 EmitAlignment(Log2_32(Size));
1482 for (const auto &Stub : Stubs) {
1483 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(Stub.first);
1484 if (DL.isFatPointer(AS))
1485 OutStreamer->EmitCheriCapability(Stub.second.getPointer(), 0, Size);
1486 else
1487 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(Stub.second.getPointer(), Size);
1488 }
1489 }
1490 }
1491
1492 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
1493 MachineModuleInfoCOFF &MMICOFF =
1494 MMI->getObjFileInfo<MachineModuleInfoCOFF>();
1495
1496 // Output stubs for external and common global variables.
1497 MachineModuleInfoCOFF::SymbolListTy Stubs = MMICOFF.GetGVStubList();
1498 if (!Stubs.empty()) {
1499 const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
1500
1501 for (const auto &Stub : Stubs) {
1502 SmallString<256> SectionName = StringRef(".rdata$");
1503 SectionName += Stub.first->getName();
1504 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(OutContext.getCOFFSection(
1505 SectionName,
1506 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ |
1507 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT,
1508 SectionKind::getReadOnly(), Stub.first->getName(),
1509 COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ANY));
1510 EmitAlignment(Log2_32(DL.getPointerSize()));
1511 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Stub.first, MCSA_Global);
1512 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(Stub.first);
1513 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(Stub.second.getPointer(),
1514 DL.getPointerSize());
1515 }
1516 }
1517 }
1518
1519 // Finalize debug and EH information.
1520 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1521 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1522 HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1523 HI.Handler->endModule();
1524 }
1525 Handlers.clear();
1526 DD = nullptr;
1527
1528 // If the target wants to know about weak references, print them all.
1529 if (MAI->getWeakRefDirective()) {
1530 // FIXME: This is not lazy, it would be nice to only print weak references
1531 // to stuff that is actually used. Note that doing so would require targets
1532 // to notice uses in operands (due to constant exprs etc). This should
1533 // happen with the MC stuff eventually.
1534
1535 // Print out module-level global objects here.
1536 for (const auto &GO : M.global_objects()) {
1537 if (!GO.hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1538 continue;
1539 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(getSymbol(&GO), MCSA_WeakReference);
1540 }
1541 }
1542
1543 OutStreamer->AddBlankLine();
1544
1545 // Print aliases in topological order, that is, for each alias a = b,
1546 // b must be printed before a.
1547 // This is because on some targets (e.g. PowerPC) linker expects aliases in
1548 // such an order to generate correct TOC information.
1549 SmallVector<const GlobalAlias *, 16> AliasStack;
1550 SmallPtrSet<const GlobalAlias *, 16> AliasVisited;
1551 for (const auto &Alias : M.aliases()) {
1552 for (const GlobalAlias *Cur = &Alias; Cur;
1553 Cur = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(Cur->getAliasee())) {
1554 if (!AliasVisited.insert(Cur).second)
1555 break;
1556 AliasStack.push_back(Cur);
1557 }
1558 for (const GlobalAlias *AncestorAlias : llvm::reverse(AliasStack))
1559 emitGlobalIndirectSymbol(M, *AncestorAlias);
1560 AliasStack.clear();
1561 }
1562 for (const auto &IFunc : M.ifuncs())
1563 emitGlobalIndirectSymbol(M, IFunc);
1564
1565 GCModuleInfo *MI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<GCModuleInfo>();
1566 assert(MI && "AsmPrinter didn't require GCModuleInfo?");
1567 for (GCModuleInfo::iterator I = MI->end(), E = MI->begin(); I != E; )
1568 if (GCMetadataPrinter *MP = GetOrCreateGCPrinter(**--I))
1569 MP->finishAssembly(M, *MI, *this);
1570
1571 // Emit llvm.ident metadata in an '.ident' directive.
1572 EmitModuleIdents(M);
1573
1574 // Emit bytes for llvm.commandline metadata.
1575 EmitModuleCommandLines(M);
1576
1577 // Emit __morestack address if needed for indirect calls.
1578 if (MMI->usesMorestackAddr()) {
1579 unsigned Align = 1;
1580 MCSection *ReadOnlySection = getObjFileLowering().getSectionForConstant(
1581 getDataLayout(), SectionKind::getReadOnly(),
1582 /*C=*/nullptr, Align);
1583 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(ReadOnlySection);
1584
1585 MCSymbol *AddrSymbol =
1586 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef("__morestack_addr"));
1587 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(AddrSymbol);
1588
1589 unsigned PtrSize = MAI->getCodePointerSize();
1590 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(GetExternalSymbolSymbol("__morestack"),
1591 PtrSize);
1592 }
1593
1594 // Emit .note.GNU-split-stack and .note.GNU-no-split-stack sections if
1595 // split-stack is used.
1596 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() && MMI->hasSplitStack()) {
1597 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(
1598 OutContext.getELFSection(".note.GNU-split-stack", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0));
1599 if (MMI->hasNosplitStack())
1600 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(
1601 OutContext.getELFSection(".note.GNU-no-split-stack", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0));
1602 }
1603
1604 // If we don't have any trampolines, then we don't require stack memory
1605 // to be executable. Some targets have a directive to declare this.
1606 Function *InitTrampolineIntrinsic = M.getFunction("llvm.init.trampoline");
1607 if (!InitTrampolineIntrinsic || InitTrampolineIntrinsic->use_empty())
1608 if (MCSection *S = MAI->getNonexecutableStackSection(OutContext))
1609 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(S);
1610
1611 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
1612 // Emit /EXPORT: flags for each exported global as necessary.
1613 const auto &TLOF = getObjFileLowering();
1614 std::string Flags;
1615
1616 for (const GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) {
1617 raw_string_ostream OS(Flags);
1618 TLOF.emitLinkerFlagsForGlobal(OS, &GV);
1619 OS.flush();
1620 if (!Flags.empty()) {
1621 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(TLOF.getDrectveSection());
1622 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(Flags);
1623 }
1624 Flags.clear();
1625 }
1626
1627 // Emit /INCLUDE: flags for each used global as necessary.
1628 if (const auto *LU = M.getNamedGlobal("llvm.used")) {
1629 assert(LU->hasInitializer() &&
1630 "expected llvm.used to have an initializer");
1631 assert(isa<ArrayType>(LU->getValueType()) &&
1632 "expected llvm.used to be an array type");
1633 if (const auto *A = cast<ConstantArray>(LU->getInitializer())) {
1634 for (const Value *Op : A->operands()) {
1635 const auto *GV =
1636 cast<GlobalValue>(Op->stripPointerCastsNoFollowAliases());
1637 // Global symbols with internal or private linkage are not visible to
1638 // the linker, and thus would cause an error when the linker tried to
1639 // preserve the symbol due to the `/include:` directive.
1640 if (GV->hasLocalLinkage())
1641 continue;
1642
1643 raw_string_ostream OS(Flags);
1644 TLOF.emitLinkerFlagsForUsed(OS, GV);
1645 OS.flush();
1646
1647 if (!Flags.empty()) {
1648 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(TLOF.getDrectveSection());
1649 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(Flags);
1650 }
1651 Flags.clear();
1652 }
1653 }
1654 }
1655 }
1656
1657 if (TM.Options.EmitAddrsig) {
1658 // Emit address-significance attributes for all globals.
1659 OutStreamer->EmitAddrsig();
1660 for (const GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values())
1661 if (!GV.use_empty() && !GV.isThreadLocal() &&
1662 !GV.hasDLLImportStorageClass() && !GV.getName().startswith("llvm.") &&
1663 !GV.hasAtLeastLocalUnnamedAddr())
1664 OutStreamer->EmitAddrsigSym(getSymbol(&GV));
1665 }
1666
1667 // Emit symbol partition specifications (ELF only).
1668 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
1669 unsigned UniqueID = 0;
1670 for (const GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) {
1671 if (!GV.hasPartition() || GV.isDeclarationForLinker() ||
1672 GV.getVisibility() != GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility)
1673 continue;
1674
1675 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(OutContext.getELFSection(
1676 ".llvm_sympart", ELF::SHT_LLVM_SYMPART, 0, 0, "", ++UniqueID));
1677 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(GV.getPartition());
1678 OutStreamer->EmitZeros(1);
1679 OutStreamer->EmitValue(
1680 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(&GV), OutContext),
1681 MAI->getCodePointerSize());
1682 }
1683 }
1684
1685 // Allow the target to emit any magic that it wants at the end of the file,
1686 // after everything else has gone out.
1687 EmitEndOfAsmFile(M);
1688
1689 MMI = nullptr;
1690
1691 OutStreamer->Finish();
1692 OutStreamer->reset();
1693 OwnedMLI.reset();
1694 OwnedMDT.reset();
1695
1696 return false;
1697}

1700 if (!CurExceptionSym)
1701 CurExceptionSym = createTempSymbol("exception");
1702 return CurExceptionSym;

1706 this->MF = &MF;
1707 // Get the function symbol.
1708 CurrentFnSym = getSymbol(&MF.getFunction());
1709 CurrentFnSymForSize = CurrentFnSym;

1721}

1723namespace {
1724
1725// Keep track the alignment, constpool entries per Section.
1726 struct SectionCPs {
1727 MCSection *S;
1728 unsigned Alignment;
1729 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> CPEs;
1730
1731 SectionCPs(MCSection *s, unsigned a) : S(s), Alignment(a) {}
1732 };
1733
1734} // end anonymous namespace
1735
1736/// EmitConstantPool - Print to the current output stream assembly
1737/// representations of the constants in the constant pool MCP. This is
1738/// used to print out constants which have been "spilled to memory" by
1739/// the code generator.
1740void AsmPrinter::EmitConstantPool() {
1741 const MachineConstantPool *MCP = MF->getConstantPool();
1742 const std::vector<MachineConstantPoolEntry> &CP = MCP->getConstants();
1743 if (CP.empty()) return;
1744
1745 // Calculate sections for constant pool entries. We collect entries to go into
1746 // the same section together to reduce amount of section switch statements.
1747 SmallVector<SectionCPs, 4> CPSections;
1748 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CP.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1749 const MachineConstantPoolEntry &CPE = CP[i];
1750 unsigned Align = CPE.getAlignment();
1751
1752 SectionKind Kind = CPE.getSectionKind(&getDataLayout());
1753
1754 const Constant *C = nullptr;
1755 if (!CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry())
1756 C = CPE.Val.ConstVal;
1757
1758 MCSection *S = getObjFileLowering().getSectionForConstant(getDataLayout(),
1759 Kind, C, Align);
1760
1761 // The number of sections are small, just do a linear search from the
1762 // last section to the first.
1763 bool Found = false;
1764 unsigned SecIdx = CPSections.size();
1765 while (SecIdx != 0) {
1766 if (CPSections[--SecIdx].S == S) {
1767 Found = true;
1768 break;
1769 }
1770 }
1771 if (!Found) {
1772 SecIdx = CPSections.size();
1773 CPSections.push_back(SectionCPs(S, Align));
1774 }
1775
1776 if (Align > CPSections[SecIdx].Alignment)
1777 CPSections[SecIdx].Alignment = Align;
1778 CPSections[SecIdx].CPEs.push_back(i);
1779 }
1780
1781 // Now print stuff into the calculated sections.
1782 const MCSection *CurSection = nullptr;
1783 unsigned Offset = 0;
1784 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPSections.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1785 for (unsigned j = 0, ee = CPSections[i].CPEs.size(); j != ee; ++j) {
1786 unsigned CPI = CPSections[i].CPEs[j];
1787 MCSymbol *Sym = GetCPISymbol(CPI);
1788 if (!Sym->isUndefined())
1789 continue;
1790
1791 if (CurSection != CPSections[i].S) {
1792 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(CPSections[i].S);
1793 EmitAlignment(Log2_32(CPSections[i].Alignment));
1794 CurSection = CPSections[i].S;
1795 Offset = 0;
1796 }
1797
1798 MachineConstantPoolEntry CPE = CP[CPI];
1799
1800 // Emit inter-object padding for alignment.
1801 unsigned AlignMask = CPE.getAlignment() - 1;
1802 unsigned NewOffset = (Offset + AlignMask) & ~AlignMask;
1803 OutStreamer->EmitZeros(NewOffset - Offset);
1804
1805 Type *Ty = CPE.getType();
1806 Offset = NewOffset + getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Ty);
1807
1808 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(Sym);
1809 if (CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry())
1810 EmitMachineConstantPoolValue(CPE.Val.MachineCPVal);
1811 else
1812 EmitGlobalConstant(getDataLayout(), CPE.Val.ConstVal, 0);
1813 }
1814 }
1815}
1816
1817/// EmitJumpTableInfo - Print assembly representations of the jump tables used
1818/// by the current function to the current output stream.
1819void AsmPrinter::EmitJumpTableInfo() {
1820 const DataLayout &DL = MF->getDataLayout();
1821 const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo();
1822 if (!MJTI) return;
1823 if (MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline) return;
1824 const std::vector<MachineJumpTableEntry> &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables();
1825 if (JT.empty()) return;
1826
1827 // Pick the directive to use to print the jump table entries, and switch to
1828 // the appropriate section.
1829 const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
1830 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = getObjFileLowering();
1831 bool JTInDiffSection = !TLOF.shouldPutJumpTableInFunctionSection(
1832 MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32,
1833 F);
1834 if (JTInDiffSection) {
1835 // Drop it in the readonly section.
1836 MCSection *ReadOnlySection = TLOF.getSectionForJumpTable(F, TM);
1837 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(ReadOnlySection);
1838 }
1839
1840 EmitAlignment(Log2_32(MJTI->getEntryAlignment(DL)));
1841
1842 // Jump tables in code sections are marked with a data_region directive
1843 // where that's supported.
1844 if (!JTInDiffSection)
1845 OutStreamer->EmitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionJT32);
1846
1847 for (unsigned JTI = 0, e = JT.size(); JTI != e; ++JTI) {
1848 const std::vector<MachineBasicBlock*> &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs;
1849
1850 // If this jump table was deleted, ignore it.
1851 if (JTBBs.empty()) continue;
1852
1853 // For the EK_LabelDifference32 entry, if using .set avoids a relocation,
1854 /// emit a .set directive for each unique entry.
1855 if (MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32 &&
1856 MAI->doesSetDirectiveSuppressReloc()) {
1857 SmallPtrSet<const MachineBasicBlock*, 16> EmittedSets;
1858 const TargetLowering *TLI = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
1859 const MCExpr *Base = TLI->getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(MF,JTI,OutContext);
1860 for (unsigned ii = 0, ee = JTBBs.size(); ii != ee; ++ii) {
1861 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = JTBBs[ii];
1862 if (!EmittedSets.insert(MBB).second)
1863 continue;
1864
1865 // .set LJTSet, LBB32-base
1866 const MCExpr *LHS =
1867 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext);
1868 OutStreamer->EmitAssignment(GetJTSetSymbol(JTI, MBB->getNumber()),
1869 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, Base,
1870 OutContext));
1871 }
1872 }
1873
1874 // On some targets (e.g. Darwin) we want to emit two consecutive labels
1875 // before each jump table. The first label is never referenced, but tells
1876 // the assembler and linker the extents of the jump table object. The
1877 // second label is actually referenced by the code.
1878 if (JTInDiffSection && DL.hasLinkerPrivateGlobalPrefix())
1879 // FIXME: This doesn't have to have any specific name, just any randomly
1880 // named and numbered 'l' label would work. Simplify GetJTISymbol.
1881 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(GetJTISymbol(JTI, true));
1882
1883 auto JTSym = GetJTISymbol(JTI);
1884 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(JTSym);
1885
1886 for (unsigned ii = 0, ee = JTBBs.size(); ii != ee; ++ii)
1887 EmitJumpTableEntry(MJTI, JTBBs[ii], JTI);
1888
1889 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective()) {
1890 auto JTEnd = createTempSymbol(JTSym->getName() + "_end");
1891 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(JTEnd);
1892 const MCExpr *SizeExp = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
1893 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JTEnd, OutContext),
1894 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JTSym, OutContext), OutContext);
1895 OutStreamer->emitELFSize(JTSym, SizeExp);
1896 }
1897 }
1898 if (!JTInDiffSection)
1899 OutStreamer->EmitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionEnd);
1900}
1901
1902/// EmitJumpTableEntry - Emit a jump table entry for the specified MBB to the
1903/// current stream.
1904void AsmPrinter::EmitJumpTableEntry(const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI,
1905 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB,
1906 unsigned UID) const {
1907 assert(MBB && MBB->getNumber() >= 0 && "Invalid basic block");
1908 const MCExpr *Value = nullptr;
1909 switch (MJTI->getEntryKind()) {
1910 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline:
1911 llvm_unreachable("Cannot emit EK_Inline jump table entry");
1912 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Custom32:
1913 Value = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering()->LowerCustomJumpTableEntry(
1914 MJTI, MBB, UID, OutContext);
1915 break;
1916 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_BlockAddress:
1917 // EK_BlockAddress - Each entry is a plain address of block, e.g.:
1918 // .word LBB123
1919 Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext);
1920 break;
1921 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel32BlockAddress: {
1922 // EK_GPRel32BlockAddress - Each entry is an address of block, encoded
1923 // with a relocation as gp-relative, e.g.:
1924 // .gprel32 LBB123
1925 MCSymbol *MBBSym = MBB->getSymbol();
1926 OutStreamer->EmitGPRel32Value(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBBSym, OutContext));
1927 return;
1928 }
1929
1930 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel64BlockAddress: {
1931 // EK_GPRel64BlockAddress - Each entry is an address of block, encoded
1932 // with a relocation as gp-relative, e.g.:
1933 // .gpdword LBB123
1934 MCSymbol *MBBSym = MBB->getSymbol();
1935 OutStreamer->EmitGPRel64Value(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBBSym, OutContext));
1936 return;
1937 }
1938
1939 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32: {
1940 // Each entry is the address of the block minus the address of the jump
1941 // table. This is used for PIC jump tables where gprel32 is not supported.
1942 // e.g.:
1943 // .word LBB123 - LJTI1_2
1944 // If the .set directive avoids relocations, this is emitted as:
1945 // .set L4_5_set_123, LBB123 - LJTI1_2
1946 // .word L4_5_set_123
1947 if (MAI->doesSetDirectiveSuppressReloc()) {
1948 Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GetJTSetSymbol(UID, MBB->getNumber()),
1949 OutContext);
1950 break;
1951 }
1952 Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext);
1953 const TargetLowering *TLI = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
1954 const MCExpr *Base = TLI->getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(MF, UID, OutContext);
1955 Value = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Value, Base, OutContext);
1956 break;
1957 }
1958 }
1959
1960 assert(Value && "Unknown entry kind!");
1961
1962 unsigned EntrySize = MJTI->getEntrySize(getDataLayout());
1963 OutStreamer->EmitValue(Value, EntrySize);
1964}
1965
1966/// EmitSpecialLLVMGlobal - Check to see if the specified global is a
1967/// special global used by LLVM. If so, emit it and return true, otherwise
1968/// do nothing and return false.
1969bool AsmPrinter::EmitSpecialLLVMGlobal(const GlobalVariable *GV) {
1970 if (GV->getName() == "llvm.used") {
1971 if (MAI->hasNoDeadStrip()) // No need to emit this at all.
1972 EmitLLVMUsedList(cast<ConstantArray>(GV->getInitializer()));
1973 return true;
1974 }
1975
1976 // Ignore debug and non-emitted data. This handles llvm.compiler.used.
1977 if (GV->getSection() == "llvm.metadata" ||
1978 GV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage())
1979 return true;
1980
1981 if (!GV->hasAppendingLinkage()) return false;
1982
1983 assert(GV->hasInitializer() && "Not a special LLVM global!");
1984
1985 if (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_ctors") {
1986 EmitXXStructorList(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(),
1987 /* isCtor */ true);
1988
1989 return true;
1990 }
1991
1992 if (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_dtors") {
1993 EmitXXStructorList(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(),
1994 /* isCtor */ false);
1995
1996 return true;
1997 }
1998
1999 report_fatal_error("unknown special variable");
2000}
2001
2002/// EmitLLVMUsedList - For targets that define a MAI::UsedDirective, mark each
2003/// global in the specified llvm.used list.
2004void AsmPrinter::EmitLLVMUsedList(const ConstantArray *InitList) {
2005 // Should be an array of 'i8*'.
2006 for (unsigned i = 0, e = InitList->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2007 const GlobalValue *GV =
2008 dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(InitList->getOperand(i)->stripPointerCasts());
2009 if (GV)
2010 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(getSymbol(GV), MCSA_NoDeadStrip);
2011 }
2012}

2014namespace {
2015
2016struct Structor {
2017 int Priority = 0;
2018 Constant *Func = nullptr;
2019 GlobalValue *ComdatKey = nullptr;
2020
2021 Structor() = default;
2022};
2023
2024} // end anonymous namespace
2025
2026/// EmitXXStructorList - Emit the ctor or dtor list taking into account the init
2027/// priority.
2028void AsmPrinter::EmitXXStructorList(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *List,
2029 bool isCtor) {
2030 // Should be an array of '{ i32, void ()*, i8* }' structs. The first value is the
2031 // init priority.
2032 if (!isa<ConstantArray>(List)) return;
2033
2034 // Sanity check the structors list.
2035 const ConstantArray *InitList = dyn_cast<ConstantArray>(List);
2036 if (!InitList) return; // Not an array!
2037 StructType *ETy = dyn_cast<StructType>(InitList->getType()->getElementType());
2038 if (!ETy || ETy->getNumElements() != 3 ||
2039 !isa<IntegerType>(ETy->getTypeAtIndex(0U)) ||
2040 !isa<PointerType>(ETy->getTypeAtIndex(1U)) ||
2041 !isa<PointerType>(ETy->getTypeAtIndex(2U)))
2042 return; // Not (int, ptr, ptr).
2043
2044 // Gather the structors in a form that's convenient for sorting by priority.
2045 SmallVector<Structor, 8> Structors;
2046 for (Value *O : InitList->operands()) {
2047 ConstantStruct *CS = dyn_cast<ConstantStruct>(O);
2048 if (!CS) continue; // Malformed.
2049 if (CS->getOperand(1)->isNullValue())
2050 break; // Found a null terminator, skip the rest.
2051 ConstantInt *Priority = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CS->getOperand(0));
2052 if (!Priority) continue; // Malformed.
2053 Structors.push_back(Structor());
2054 Structor &S = Structors.back();
2055 S.Priority = Priority->getLimitedValue(65535);
2056 S.Func = CS->getOperand(1);
2057 if (!CS->getOperand(2)->isNullValue())
2058 S.ComdatKey =
2059 dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(CS->getOperand(2)->stripPointerCasts());
2060 }
2061
2062 // Emit the function pointers in the target-specific order
2063 unsigned Align = Log2_32(DL.getPointerPrefAlignment());
2064 llvm::stable_sort(Structors, [](const Structor &L, const Structor &R) {
2065 return L.Priority < R.Priority;
2066 });
2067 for (Structor &S : Structors) {
2068 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &Obj = getObjFileLowering();
2069 const MCSymbol *KeySym = nullptr;
2070 if (GlobalValue *GV = S.ComdatKey) {
2071 if (GV->isDeclarationForLinker())
2072 // If the associated variable is not defined in this module
2073 // (it might be available_externally, or have been an
2074 // available_externally definition that was dropped by the
2075 // EliminateAvailableExternally pass), some other TU
2076 // will provide its dynamic initializer.
2077 continue;
2078
2079 KeySym = getSymbol(GV);
2080 }
2081 MCSection *OutputSection =
2082 (isCtor ? Obj.getStaticCtorSection(S.Priority, KeySym)
2083 : Obj.getStaticDtorSection(S.Priority, KeySym));
2084 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(OutputSection);
2085 if (OutStreamer->getCurrentSection() != OutStreamer->getPreviousSection())
2086 EmitAlignment(Align);
2087 EmitXXStructor(DL, S.Func);
2088 }
2089}

2091void AsmPrinter::EmitModuleIdents(Module &M) {
2092 if (!MAI->hasIdentDirective())
2093 return;
2094
2095 if (const NamedMDNode *NMD = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.ident")) {
2096 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NMD->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2097 const MDNode *N = NMD->getOperand(i);
2098 assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1 &&
2099 "llvm.ident metadata entry can have only one operand");
2100 const MDString *S = cast<MDString>(N->getOperand(0));
2101 OutStreamer->EmitIdent(S->getString());
2102 }
2103 }

2106void AsmPrinter::EmitModuleCommandLines(Module &M) {
2107 MCSection *CommandLine = getObjFileLowering().getSectionForCommandLines();
2108 if (!CommandLine)
2109 return;
2110
2111 const NamedMDNode *NMD = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.commandline");
2112 if (!NMD || !NMD->getNumOperands())
2113 return;
2114
2115 OutStreamer->PushSection();
2116 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(CommandLine);
2117 OutStreamer->EmitZeros(1);
2118 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NMD->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2119 const MDNode *N = NMD->getOperand(i);
2120 assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1 &&
2121 "llvm.commandline metadata entry can have only one operand");
2122 const MDString *S = cast<MDString>(N->getOperand(0));
2123 OutStreamer->EmitBytes(S->getString());
2124 OutStreamer->EmitZeros(1);
2125 }
2126 OutStreamer->PopSection();
2127}

2162/// EmitLabelPlusOffset - Emit something like ".long Label+Offset"

2164/// specifies the label. This implicitly uses .set if it is available.

2166 unsigned Size,
2167 bool IsSectionRelative) const {

2169 OutStreamer->EmitCOFFSecRel32(Label, Offset);

2171 OutStreamer->EmitZeros(Size - 4);

2186// EmitAlignment - Emit an alignment directive to the specified power of
2187// two boundary. For example, if you pass in 3 here, you will get an 8
2188// byte alignment. If a global value is specified, and if that global has
2189// an explicit alignment requested, it will override the alignment request
2190// if required for correctness.
2191void AsmPrinter::EmitAlignment(unsigned NumBits, const GlobalObject *GV) const {
2192 if (GV)
2193 NumBits = getGVAlignmentLog2(GV, GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), NumBits);
2194
2195 if (NumBits == 0) return; // 1-byte aligned: no need to emit alignment.
2196
2197 assert(NumBits <
2198 static_cast<unsigned>(std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::digits) &&
2199 "undefined behavior");
2200 if (getCurrentSection()->getKind().isText())
2201 OutStreamer->EmitCodeAlignment(1u << NumBits);
2202 else
2203 OutStreamer->EmitValueToAlignment(1u << NumBits);
2204}

2206//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2207// Constant emission.
2208//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2209
2210const MCExpr *AsmPrinter::lowerConstant(const Constant *CV) {
2211 MCContext &Ctx = OutContext;
2212
2213 if (CV->isNullValue() || isa<UndefValue>(CV))
2214 return MCConstantExpr::create(0, Ctx);
2215
2216 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CV))
2217 return MCConstantExpr::create(CI->getZExtValue(), Ctx);
2218
2219 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(CV))
2220 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(GV), Ctx);
2221
2222 if (const BlockAddress *BA = dyn_cast<BlockAddress>(CV))
2223 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GetBlockAddressSymbol(BA), Ctx);
2224
2225 const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(CV);
2226 if (!CE) {
2227 llvm_unreachable("Unknown constant value to lower!");
2228 }
2229
2230 switch (CE->getOpcode()) {
2231 default:
2232 // If the code isn't optimized, there may be outstanding folding
2233 // opportunities. Attempt to fold the expression using DataLayout as a
2234 // last resort before giving up.
2235 if (Constant *C = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, getDataLayout()))
2236 if (C != CE)
2237 return lowerConstant(C);
2238
2239 // Otherwise report the problem to the user.
2240 {
2241 std::string S;
2242 raw_string_ostream OS(S);
2243 OS << "Unsupported expression in static initializer: ";
2244 CE->printAsOperand(OS, /*PrintType=*/false,
2245 !MF ? nullptr : MF->getFunction().getParent());
2246 report_fatal_error(OS.str());
2247 }
2248
2249 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: {
2250 return lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
2251 }
2252
2253 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: {
2254 // Generate a symbolic expression for the byte address
2255 APInt OffsetAI(getDataLayout().getPointerBaseSizeInBits(CE->getType()), 0);
2256 cast<GEPOperator>(CE)->accumulateConstantOffset(getDataLayout(), OffsetAI);
2257
2258 const MCExpr *Base = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
2259 if (!OffsetAI)
2260 return Base;
2261
2262 int64_t Offset = OffsetAI.getSExtValue();
2263 return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Base, MCConstantExpr::create(Offset, Ctx),
2264 Ctx);
2265 }
2266
2267 case Instruction::Trunc:
2268 // We emit the value and depend on the assembler to truncate the generated
2269 // expression properly. This is important for differences between
2270 // blockaddress labels. Since the two labels are in the same function, it
2271 // is reasonable to treat their delta as a 32-bit value.
2272 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2273 case Instruction::BitCast:
2274 return lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
2275
2276 case Instruction::IntToPtr: {
2277 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
2278
2279 // Handle casts to pointers by changing them into casts to the appropriate
2280 // integer type. This promotes constant folding and simplifies this code.
2281 Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0);
2282 Op = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(Op, DL.getIntPtrType(CV->getType()),
2283 false/*ZExt*/);
2284 return lowerConstant(Op);
2285 }
2286
2287 case Instruction::PtrToInt: {
2288 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
2289
2290 // Support only foldable casts to/from pointers that can be eliminated by
2291 // changing the pointer to the appropriately sized integer type.
2292 Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0);
2293 Type *Ty = CE->getType();
2294
2295 const MCExpr *OpExpr = lowerConstant(Op);
2296
2297 // We can emit the pointer value into this slot if the slot is an
2298 // integer slot equal to the size of the pointer.
2299 //
2300 // If the pointer is larger than the resultant integer, then
2301 // as with Trunc just depend on the assembler to truncate it.
2302 if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty) <= DL.getTypeAllocSize(Op->getType()))
2303 return OpExpr;
2304 if (Op->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() &&
2305 DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty) == DL.getPointerBaseSize(Op->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()))
2306 return OpExpr;
2307 assert(!DL.isFatPointer(Op->getType()) && "Fat pointer should not be masked when lowering constant.");
2308
2309 // Otherwise the pointer is smaller than the resultant integer, mask off
2310 // the high bits so we are sure to get a proper truncation if the input is
2311 // a constant expr.
2312 unsigned InBits = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(Op->getType());
2313 const MCExpr *MaskExpr = MCConstantExpr::create(~0ULL >> (64-InBits), Ctx);
2314
2315 return MCBinaryExpr::createAnd(OpExpr, MaskExpr, Ctx);
2316 }
2317
2318 case Instruction::Sub: {
2319 GlobalValue *LHSGV;
2320 APInt LHSOffset;
2321 if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(CE->getOperand(0), LHSGV, LHSOffset,
2322 getDataLayout(), false)) {
2323 GlobalValue *RHSGV;
2324 APInt RHSOffset;
2325 if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(CE->getOperand(1), RHSGV, RHSOffset,
2326 getDataLayout(), false)) {
2327 const MCExpr *RelocExpr =
2328 getObjFileLowering().lowerRelativeReference(LHSGV, RHSGV, TM);
2329 if (!RelocExpr)
2330 RelocExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
2331 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(LHSGV), Ctx),
2332 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(RHSGV), Ctx), Ctx);
2333 int64_t Addend = (LHSOffset - RHSOffset).getSExtValue();
2334 if (Addend != 0)
2335 RelocExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(
2336 RelocExpr, MCConstantExpr::create(Addend, Ctx), Ctx);
2337 return RelocExpr;
2338 }
2339 }
2340 }
2341 // else fallthrough
2342 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2343
2344 // The MC library also has a right-shift operator, but it isn't consistently
2345 // signed or unsigned between different targets.
2346 case Instruction::Add:
2347 case Instruction::Mul:
2348 case Instruction::SDiv:
2349 case Instruction::SRem:
2350 case Instruction::Shl:
2351 case Instruction::And:
2352 case Instruction::Or:
2353 case Instruction::Xor: {
2354 const MCExpr *LHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
2355 const MCExpr *RHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(1));
2356 switch (CE->getOpcode()) {
2357 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown binary operator constant cast expr");
2358 case Instruction::Add: return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2359 case Instruction::Sub: return MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2360 case Instruction::Mul: return MCBinaryExpr::createMul(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2361 case Instruction::SDiv: return MCBinaryExpr::createDiv(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2362 case Instruction::SRem: return MCBinaryExpr::createMod(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2363 case Instruction::Shl: return MCBinaryExpr::createShl(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2364 case Instruction::And: return MCBinaryExpr::createAnd(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2365 case Instruction::Or: return MCBinaryExpr::createOr (LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2366 case Instruction::Xor: return MCBinaryExpr::createXor(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
2367 }
2368 }
2369 }
2370}
