2380/// isRepeatedByteSequence - Determine whether the given value is
2381/// composed of a repeated sequence of identical bytes and return the
2382/// byte value. If it is not a repeated sequence, return -1.
2383static int isRepeatedByteSequence(const ConstantDataSequential *V) {
2384 StringRef Data = V->getRawDataValues();
2385 assert(!Data.empty() && "Empty aggregates should be CAZ node");
2386 char C = Data[0];
2387 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Data.size(); i != e; ++i)
2388 if (Data[i] != C) return -1;
2389 return static_cast<uint8_t>(C); // Ensure 255 is not returned as -1.
2390}
2391
2392/// isRepeatedByteSequence - Determine whether the given value is
2393/// composed of a repeated sequence of identical bytes and return the
2394/// byte value. If it is not a repeated sequence, return -1.
2395static int isRepeatedByteSequence(const Value *V, const DataLayout &DL) {
2396 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(V)) {
2397 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(V->getType());
2398 assert(Size % 8 == 0);
2399
2400 // Extend the element to take zero padding into account.
2401 APInt Value = CI->getValue().zextOrSelf(Size);
2402 if (!Value.isSplat(8))
2403 return -1;
2404
2405 return Value.zextOrTrunc(8).getZExtValue();
2406 }
2407 if (const ConstantArray *CA = dyn_cast<ConstantArray>(V)) {
2408 // Make sure all array elements are sequences of the same repeated
2409 // byte.
2410 assert(CA->getNumOperands() != 0 && "Should be a CAZ");
2411 Constant *Op0 = CA->getOperand(0);
2412 int Byte = isRepeatedByteSequence(Op0, DL);
2413 if (Byte == -1)
2414 return -1;
2415
2416 // All array elements must be equal.
2417 for (unsigned i = 1, e = CA->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i)
2418 if (CA->getOperand(i) != Op0)
2419 return -1;
2420 return Byte;
2421 }
2422
2423 if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = dyn_cast<ConstantDataSequential>(V))
2424 return isRepeatedByteSequence(CDS);
2425
2426 return -1;
2427}
2428
2429static void emitGlobalConstantDataSequential(const DataLayout &DL,
2430 const ConstantDataSequential *CDS,
2431 AsmPrinter &AP) {
2432 // See if we can aggregate this into a .fill, if so, emit it as such.
2433 int Value = isRepeatedByteSequence(CDS, DL);
2434 if (Value != -1) {
2435 uint64_t Bytes = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType());
2436 // Don't emit a 1-byte object as a .fill.
2437 if (Bytes > 1)
2438 return AP.OutStreamer->emitFill(Bytes, Value);
2439 }
2440
2441 // If this can be emitted with .ascii/.asciz, emit it as such.
2442 if (CDS->isString())
2443 return AP.OutStreamer->EmitBytes(CDS->getAsString());
2444
2445 // Otherwise, emit the values in successive locations.
2446 unsigned ElementByteSize = CDS->getElementByteSize();
2447 if (isa<IntegerType>(CDS->getElementType())) {
2448 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CDS->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2449 if (AP.isVerbose())
2450 AP.OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << format("0x%" PRIx64 "\n",
2451 CDS->getElementAsInteger(i));
2452 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(CDS->getElementAsInteger(i),
2453 ElementByteSize);
2454 }
2455 } else {
2456 Type *ET = CDS->getElementType();
2457 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CDS->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I)
2458 emitGlobalConstantFP(CDS->getElementAsAPFloat(I), ET, AP);
2459 }
2460
2461 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType());
2462 unsigned EmittedSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType()->getElementType()) *
2463 CDS->getNumElements();
2464 assert(EmittedSize <= Size && "Size cannot be less than EmittedSize!");
2465 if (unsigned Padding = Size - EmittedSize)
2466 AP.OutStreamer->EmitZeros(Padding);
2467}
2468
2469static void emitGlobalConstantArray(const DataLayout &DL,
2470 const ConstantArray *CA, AsmPrinter &AP,
2471 const Constant *BaseCV, uint64_t Offset) {
2472 // See if we can aggregate some values. Make sure it can be
2473 // represented as a series of bytes of the constant value.
2474 int Value = isRepeatedByteSequence(CA, DL);
2475
2476 if (Value != -1) {
2477 uint64_t Bytes = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CA->getType());
2478 AP.OutStreamer->emitFill(Bytes, Value);
2479 }
2480 else {
2481 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CA->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2482 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CA->getOperand(i), AP, BaseCV, Offset);
2483 Offset += DL.getTypeAllocSize(CA->getOperand(i)->getType());
2484 }
2485 }
2486}
2487
2488static void emitGlobalConstantVector(const DataLayout &DL,
2489 const ConstantVector *CV, AsmPrinter &AP) {
2490 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CV->getType()->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i)
2491 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CV->getOperand(i), AP);
2492
2493 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType());
2494 unsigned EmittedSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType()->getElementType()) *
2495 CV->getType()->getNumElements();
2496 if (unsigned Padding = Size - EmittedSize)
2497 AP.OutStreamer->EmitZeros(Padding);
2498}
2499
2500static void emitGlobalConstantStruct(const DataLayout &DL,
2501 const ConstantStruct *CS, AsmPrinter &AP,
2502 const Constant *BaseCV, uint64_t Offset) {
2503 // Print the fields in successive locations. Pad to align if needed!
2504 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CS->getType());
2505 const StructLayout *Layout = DL.getStructLayout(CS->getType());
2506 uint64_t SizeSoFar = 0;
2507 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CS->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2508 const Constant *Field = CS->getOperand(i);
2509
2510 // Print the actual field value.
2511 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, Field, AP, BaseCV, Offset + SizeSoFar);
2512
2513 // Check if padding is needed and insert one or more 0s.
2514 uint64_t FieldSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(Field->getType());
2515 uint64_t PadSize = ((i == e-1 ? Size : Layout->getElementOffset(i+1))
2516 - Layout->getElementOffset(i)) - FieldSize;
2517 SizeSoFar += FieldSize + PadSize;
2518
2519 // Insert padding - this may include padding to increase the size of the
2520 // current field up to the ABI size (if the struct is not packed) as well
2521 // as padding to ensure that the next field starts at the right offset.
2522 AP.OutStreamer->EmitZeros(PadSize);
2523 }
2524 assert(SizeSoFar == Layout->getSizeInBytes() &&
2525 "Layout of constant struct may be incorrect!");
2526}
2527
2528static void emitGlobalConstantFP(APFloat APF, Type *ET, AsmPrinter &AP) {
2529 APInt API = APF.bitcastToAPInt();
2530
2531 // First print a comment with what we think the original floating-point value
2532 // should have been.
2533 if (AP.isVerbose()) {
2534 SmallString<8> StrVal;
2535 APF.toString(StrVal);
2536
2537 if (ET)
2538 ET->print(AP.OutStreamer->GetCommentOS());
2539 else
2540 AP.OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << "Printing <null> Type";
2541 AP.OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << ' ' << StrVal << '\n';
2542 }
2543
2544 // Now iterate through the APInt chunks, emitting them in endian-correct
2545 // order, possibly with a smaller chunk at beginning/end (e.g. for x87 80-bit
2546 // floats).
2547 unsigned NumBytes = API.getBitWidth() / 8;
2548 unsigned TrailingBytes = NumBytes % sizeof(uint64_t);
2549 const uint64_t *p = API.getRawData();
2550
2551 // PPC's long double has odd notions of endianness compared to how LLVM
2552 // handles it: p[0] goes first for *big* endian on PPC.
2553 if (AP.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() && !ET->isPPC_FP128Ty()) {
2554 int Chunk = API.getNumWords() - 1;
2555
2556 if (TrailingBytes)
2557 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(p[Chunk--], TrailingBytes);
2558
2559 for (; Chunk >= 0; --Chunk)
2560 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(p[Chunk], sizeof(uint64_t));
2561 } else {
2562 unsigned Chunk;
2563 for (Chunk = 0; Chunk < NumBytes / sizeof(uint64_t); ++Chunk)
2564 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(p[Chunk], sizeof(uint64_t));
2565
2566 if (TrailingBytes)
2567 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(p[Chunk], TrailingBytes);
2568 }
2569
2570 // Emit the tail padding for the long double.
2571 const DataLayout &DL = AP.getDataLayout();
2572 AP.OutStreamer->EmitZeros(DL.getTypeAllocSize(ET) - DL.getTypeStoreSize(ET));
2573}
2574
2575static void emitGlobalConstantFP(const ConstantFP *CFP, AsmPrinter &AP) {
2576 emitGlobalConstantFP(CFP->getValueAPF(), CFP->getType(), AP);
2577}
2578
2579static void emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(const ConstantInt *CI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
2580 const DataLayout &DL = AP.getDataLayout();
2581 unsigned BitWidth = CI->getBitWidth();
2582
2583 // Copy the value as we may massage the layout for constants whose bit width
2584 // is not a multiple of 64-bits.
2585 APInt Realigned(CI->getValue());
2586 uint64_t ExtraBits = 0;
2587 unsigned ExtraBitsSize = BitWidth & 63;
2588
2589 if (ExtraBitsSize) {
2590 // The bit width of the data is not a multiple of 64-bits.
2591 // The extra bits are expected to be at the end of the chunk of the memory.
2592 // Little endian:
2593 // * Nothing to be done, just record the extra bits to emit.
2594 // Big endian:
2595 // * Record the extra bits to emit.
2596 // * Realign the raw data to emit the chunks of 64-bits.
2597 if (DL.isBigEndian()) {
2598 // Basically the structure of the raw data is a chunk of 64-bits cells:
2599 // 0 1 BitWidth / 64
2600 // [chunk1][chunk2] ... [chunkN].
2601 // The most significant chunk is chunkN and it should be emitted first.
2602 // However, due to the alignment issue chunkN contains useless bits.
2603 // Realign the chunks so that they contain only useless information:
2604 // ExtraBits 0 1 (BitWidth / 64) - 1
2605 // chu[nk1 chu][nk2 chu] ... [nkN-1 chunkN]
2606 ExtraBits = Realigned.getRawData()[0] &
2607 (((uint64_t)-1) >> (64 - ExtraBitsSize));
2608 Realigned.lshrInPlace(ExtraBitsSize);
2609 } else
2610 ExtraBits = Realigned.getRawData()[BitWidth / 64];
2611 }
2612
2613 // We don't expect assemblers to support integer data directives
2614 // for more than 64 bits, so we emit the data in at most 64-bit
2615 // quantities at a time.
2616 const uint64_t *RawData = Realigned.getRawData();
2617 for (unsigned i = 0, e = BitWidth / 64; i != e; ++i) {
2618 uint64_t Val = DL.isBigEndian() ? RawData[e - i - 1] : RawData[i];
2619 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(Val, 8);
2620 }
2621
2622 if (ExtraBitsSize) {
2623 // Emit the extra bits after the 64-bits chunks.
2624
2625 // Emit a directive that fills the expected size.
2626 uint64_t Size = AP.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(CI->getType());
2627 Size -= (BitWidth / 64) * 8;
2628 assert(Size && Size * 8 >= ExtraBitsSize &&
2629 (ExtraBits & (((uint64_t)-1) >> (64 - ExtraBitsSize)))
2630 == ExtraBits && "Directive too small for extra bits.");
2631 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(ExtraBits, Size);
2632 }
2633}
2634
2635/// Transform a not absolute MCExpr containing a reference to a GOT
2636/// equivalent global, by a target specific GOT pc relative access to the
2637/// final symbol.
2638static void handleIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(AsmPrinter &AP, const MCExpr **ME,
2639 const Constant *BaseCst,
2640 uint64_t Offset) {
2641 // The global @foo below illustrates a global that uses a got equivalent.
2642 //
2643 // @bar = global i32 42
2644 // @gotequiv = private unnamed_addr constant i32* @bar
2645 // @foo = i32 trunc (i64 sub (i64 ptrtoint (i32** @gotequiv to i64),
2646 // i64 ptrtoint (i32* @foo to i64))
2647 // to i32)
2648 //
2649 // The cstexpr in @foo is converted into the MCExpr `ME`, where we actually
2650 // check whether @foo is suitable to use a GOTPCREL. `ME` is usually in the
2651 // form:
2652 //
2653 // foo = cstexpr, where
2654 // cstexpr := <gotequiv> - "." + <cst>
2655 // cstexpr := <gotequiv> - (<foo> - <offset from @foo base>) + <cst>
2656 //
2657 // After canonicalization by evaluateAsRelocatable `ME` turns into:
2658 //
2659 // cstexpr := <gotequiv> - <foo> + gotpcrelcst, where
2660 // gotpcrelcst := <offset from @foo base> + <cst>
2661 MCValue MV;
2662 if (!(*ME)->evaluateAsRelocatable(MV, nullptr, nullptr) || MV.isAbsolute())
2663 return;
2664 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SymA = MV.getSymA();
2665 if (!SymA)
2666 return;
2667
2668 // Check that GOT equivalent symbol is cached.
2669 const MCSymbol *GOTEquivSym = &SymA->getSymbol();
2670 if (!AP.GlobalGOTEquivs.count(GOTEquivSym))
2671 return;
2672
2673 const GlobalValue *BaseGV = dyn_cast_or_null<GlobalValue>(BaseCst);
2674 if (!BaseGV)
2675 return;
2676
2677 // Check for a valid base symbol
2678 const MCSymbol *BaseSym = AP.getSymbol(BaseGV);
2679 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SymB = MV.getSymB();
2680
2681 if (!SymB || BaseSym != &SymB->getSymbol())
2682 return;
2683
2684 // Make sure to match:
2685 //
2686 // gotpcrelcst := <offset from @foo base> + <cst>
2687 //
2688 // If gotpcrelcst is positive it means that we can safely fold the pc rel
2689 // displacement into the GOTPCREL. We can also can have an extra offset <cst>
2690 // if the target knows how to encode it.
2691 int64_t GOTPCRelCst = Offset + MV.getConstant();
2692 if (GOTPCRelCst < 0)
2693 return;
2694 if (!AP.getObjFileLowering().supportGOTPCRelWithOffset() && GOTPCRelCst != 0)
2695 return;
2696
2697 // Emit the GOT PC relative to replace the got equivalent global, i.e.:
2698 //
2699 // bar:
2700 // .long 42
2701 // gotequiv:
2702 // .quad bar
2703 // foo:
2704 // .long gotequiv - "." + <cst>
2705 //
2706 // is replaced by the target specific equivalent to:
2707 //
2708 // bar:
2709 // .long 42
2710 // foo:
2711 // .long bar@GOTPCREL+<gotpcrelcst>
2712 AsmPrinter::GOTEquivUsePair Result = AP.GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym];
2713 const GlobalVariable *GV = Result.first;
2714 int NumUses = (int)Result.second;
2715 const GlobalValue *FinalGV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(GV->getOperand(0));
2716 const MCSymbol *FinalSym = AP.getSymbol(FinalGV);
2717 *ME = AP.getObjFileLowering().getIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(
2718 FinalSym, MV, Offset, AP.MMI, *AP.OutStreamer);
2719
2720 // Update GOT equivalent usage information
2721 --NumUses;
2722 if (NumUses >= 0)
2723 AP.GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym] = std::make_pair(GV, NumUses);
2724}
2725
2726static void emitGlobalConstantCHERICap(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV,
2727 AsmPrinter &AP) {
2728 const uint64_t CapWidth = DL.getPointerTypeSize(CV->getType());
2729 // Handle (void *)5 etc as an untagged capability with base/length/perms 0,
2730 // and offset 5.
2731 const MCExpr *Expr = AP.lowerConstant(CV);
2732 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr)) {
2733 AP.OutStreamer->EmitCheriIntcap(CE->getValue(), CapWidth);
2734 return;
2735 }
2736 GlobalValue *GV;
2737 APInt Addend;
2738 if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(const_cast<Constant *>(CV), GV, Addend, DL,
2739 true)) {
2740 AP.OutStreamer->EmitCheriCapability(AP.getSymbol(GV), Addend.getSExtValue(),
2741 CapWidth);
2742 return;
2743 } else if (const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = dyn_cast<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr)) {
2744 // emit capability for label whose address is stored in a global variable
2745 // FIXME: this is wrong
2746 if (SRE->getSymbol().isTemporary()) {
2747 report_fatal_error(
2748 "Cannot emit a global .chericap referring to a temporary since this "
2749 "will result in the wrong value at runtime!");
2750 AP.OutStreamer->EmitCheriCapability(&SRE->getSymbol(), 0, CapWidth);
2751 return;
2752 }
2753 }
2754 llvm_unreachable("Tried to emit a capability which is neither a constant nor "
2755 "a global+offset");
2756}
2757
2758static void emitGlobalConstantImpl(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV,
2759 AsmPrinter &AP, const Constant *BaseCV,
2760 uint64_t Offset) {
2761 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType());
2762
2763 // Globals with sub-elements such as combinations of arrays and structs
2764 // are handled recursively by emitGlobalConstantImpl. Keep track of the
2765 // constant symbol base and the current position with BaseCV and Offset.
2766 if (!BaseCV && CV->hasOneUse())
2767 BaseCV = dyn_cast<Constant>(CV->user_back());
2768
2769 if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(CV) || isa<UndefValue>(CV))
2770 return AP.OutStreamer->EmitZeros(Size);
2771
2772 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CV)) {
2773 switch (Size) {
2774 case 1:
2775 case 2:
2776 case 4:
2777 case 8:
2778 if (AP.isVerbose())
2779 AP.OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << format("0x%" PRIx64 "\n",
2780 CI->getZExtValue());
2781 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(CI->getZExtValue(), Size);
2782 return;
2783 default:
2784 emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(CI, AP);
2785 return;
2786 }
2787 }
2788
2789 if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(CV))
2790 return emitGlobalConstantFP(CFP, AP);
2791
2792 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(CV)) {
2793 if (CV->getType()->isPointerTy() && DL.isFatPointer(CV->getType()))
2794 AP.OutStreamer->EmitCheriIntcap(0, Size);
2795 else
2796 AP.OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(0, Size);
2797 return;
2798 }
2799
2800 if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = dyn_cast<ConstantDataSequential>(CV))
2801 return emitGlobalConstantDataSequential(DL, CDS, AP);
2802
2803 if (const ConstantArray *CVA = dyn_cast<ConstantArray>(CV))
2804 return emitGlobalConstantArray(DL, CVA, AP, BaseCV, Offset);
2805
2806 if (const ConstantStruct *CVS = dyn_cast<ConstantStruct>(CV))
2807 return emitGlobalConstantStruct(DL, CVS, AP, BaseCV, Offset);
2808
2809 if (const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(CV)) {
2810 // Look through bitcasts, which might not be able to be MCExpr'ized (e.g. of
2811 // vectors).
2812 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::BitCast)
2813 return emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CE->getOperand(0), AP);
2814
2815 if (Size > 8) {
2816 // If the constant expression's size is greater than 64-bits, then we have
2817 // to emit the value in chunks. Try to constant fold the value and emit it
2818 // that way.
2819 Constant *New = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, DL);
2820 if (New && New != CE)
2821 return emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, New, AP);
2822 }
2823 }
2824
2825 if (const ConstantVector *V = dyn_cast<ConstantVector>(CV))
2826 return emitGlobalConstantVector(DL, V, AP);
2827
2828 if (CV->getType()->isPointerTy() && DL.isFatPointer(CV->getType()))
2829 return emitGlobalConstantCHERICap(DL, CV, AP);
2830
2831 // Otherwise, it must be a ConstantExpr. Lower it to an MCExpr, then emit it
2832 // thread the streamer with EmitValue.
2833 const MCExpr *ME = AP.lowerConstant(CV);
2834
2835 // Since lowerConstant already folded and got rid of all IR pointer and
2836 // integer casts, detect GOT equivalent accesses by looking into the MCExpr
2837 // directly.
2838 if (AP.getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel())
2839 handleIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(AP, &ME, BaseCV, Offset);
2840
2841 AP.OutStreamer->EmitValue(ME, Size);
2842}
2843
2844/// EmitGlobalConstant - Print a general LLVM constant to the .s file.
2845void AsmPrinter::EmitGlobalConstant(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV,
2846 unsigned TailPadding) {
2847 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType());
2848 if (Size)
2849 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CV, *this);
2850 else if (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols()) {
2851 // If the global has zero size, emit a single byte so that two labels don't
2852 // look like they are at the same location.
2853 OutStreamer->EmitIntValue(0, 1);
2854 }
2855 if (TailPadding != 0) {
2856 OutStreamer->AddComment("Tail padding to ensure precise bounds");
2857 OutStreamer->EmitZeros(TailPadding);
2858 }
2859}

2942/// PrintParentLoopComment - Print comments about parent loops of this one.
2943static void PrintParentLoopComment(raw_ostream &OS, const MachineLoop *Loop,
2944 unsigned FunctionNumber) {
2945 if (!Loop) return;
2946 PrintParentLoopComment(OS, Loop->getParentLoop(), FunctionNumber);
2947 OS.indent(Loop->getLoopDepth()*2)
2948 << "Parent Loop BB" << FunctionNumber << "_"
2949 << Loop->getHeader()->getNumber()
2950 << " Depth=" << Loop->getLoopDepth() << '\n';
2951}

2953/// PrintChildLoopComment - Print comments about child loops within
2954/// the loop for this basic block, with nesting.
2955static void PrintChildLoopComment(raw_ostream &OS, const MachineLoop *Loop,
2956 unsigned FunctionNumber) {
2957 // Add child loop information
2958 for (const MachineLoop *CL : *Loop) {
2959 OS.indent(CL->getLoopDepth()*2)
2960 << "Child Loop BB" << FunctionNumber << "_"
2961 << CL->getHeader()->getNumber() << " Depth " << CL->getLoopDepth()
2962 << '\n';
2963 PrintChildLoopComment(OS, CL, FunctionNumber);
2964 }
2965}
2966
2967/// emitBasicBlockLoopComments - Pretty-print comments for basic blocks.
2968static void emitBasicBlockLoopComments(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
2969 const MachineLoopInfo *LI,
2970 const AsmPrinter &AP) {
2971 // Add loop depth information
2972 const MachineLoop *Loop = LI->getLoopFor(&MBB);
2973 if (!Loop) return;
2974
2975 MachineBasicBlock *Header = Loop->getHeader();
2976 assert(Header && "No header for loop");
2977
2978 // If this block is not a loop header, just print out what is the loop header
2979 // and return.
2980 if (Header != &MBB) {
2981 AP.OutStreamer->AddComment(" in Loop: Header=BB" +
2982 Twine(AP.getFunctionNumber())+"_" +
2983 Twine(Loop->getHeader()->getNumber())+
2984 " Depth="+Twine(Loop->getLoopDepth()));
2985 return;
2986 }
2987
2988 // Otherwise, it is a loop header. Print out information about child and
2989 // parent loops.
2990 raw_ostream &OS = AP.OutStreamer->GetCommentOS();
2991
2992 PrintParentLoopComment(OS, Loop->getParentLoop(), AP.getFunctionNumber());
2993
2994 OS << "=>";
2995 OS.indent(Loop->getLoopDepth()*2-2);
2996
2997 OS << "This ";
2998 if (Loop->empty())
2999 OS << "Inner ";
3000 OS << "Loop Header: Depth=" + Twine(Loop->getLoopDepth()) << '\n';
3001
3002 PrintChildLoopComment(OS, Loop, AP.getFunctionNumber());
3003}

3005void AsmPrinter::setupCodePaddingContext(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
3006 MCCodePaddingContext &Context) const {
3007 assert(MF != nullptr && "Machine function must be valid");
3008 Context.IsPaddingActive = !MF->hasInlineAsm() &&
3009 !MF->getFunction().hasOptSize() &&
3010 TM.getOptLevel() != CodeGenOpt::None;
3011 Context.IsBasicBlockReachableViaFallthrough =
3012 std::find(MBB.pred_begin(), MBB.pred_end(), MBB.getPrevNode()) !=
3013 MBB.pred_end();
3014 Context.IsBasicBlockReachableViaBranch =
3015 MBB.pred_size() > 0 && !isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthrough(&MBB);
3016}

3018/// EmitBasicBlockStart - This method prints the label for the specified
3019/// MachineBasicBlock, an alignment (if present) and a comment describing
3020/// it if appropriate.
3021void AsmPrinter::EmitBasicBlockStart(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) const {
3022 // End the previous funclet and start a new one.
3023 if (MBB.isEHFuncletEntry()) {
3024 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
3025 HI.Handler->endFunclet();
3026 HI.Handler->beginFunclet(MBB);
3027 }
3028 }
3029
3030 // Emit an alignment directive for this block, if needed.
3031 if (unsigned Align = MBB.getAlignment())
3032 EmitAlignment(Align);
3033 MCCodePaddingContext Context;
3034 setupCodePaddingContext(MBB, Context);
3035 OutStreamer->EmitCodePaddingBasicBlockStart(Context);
3036
3037 // If the block has its address taken, emit any labels that were used to
3038 // reference the block. It is possible that there is more than one label
3039 // here, because multiple LLVM BB's may have been RAUW'd to this block after
3040 // the references were generated.
3041 if (MBB.hasAddressTaken()) {
3042 const BasicBlock *BB = MBB.getBasicBlock();
3043 if (isVerbose())
3044 OutStreamer->AddComment("Block address taken");
3045
3046 // MBBs can have their address taken as part of CodeGen without having
3047 // their corresponding BB's address taken in IR
3048 if (BB->hasAddressTaken())
3049 for (MCSymbol *Sym : MMI->getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(BB))
3050 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(Sym);
3051 }
3052
3053 // Print some verbose block comments.
3054 if (isVerbose()) {
3055 if (const BasicBlock *BB = MBB.getBasicBlock()) {
3056 if (BB->hasName()) {
3057 BB->printAsOperand(OutStreamer->GetCommentOS(),
3058 /*PrintType=*/false, BB->getModule());
3059 OutStreamer->GetCommentOS() << '\n';
3060 }
3061 }
3062
3063 assert(MLI != nullptr && "MachineLoopInfo should has been computed");
3064 emitBasicBlockLoopComments(MBB, MLI, *this);
3065 }
3066
3067 // Print the main label for the block.
3068 if (MBB.pred_empty() ||
3069 (isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthrough(&MBB) && !MBB.isEHFuncletEntry() &&
3070 !MBB.hasLabelMustBeEmitted())) {
3071 if (isVerbose()) {
3072 // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
3073 OutStreamer->emitRawComment(" %bb." + Twine(MBB.getNumber()) + ":",
3074 false);
3075 }
3076 } else {
3077 if (isVerbose() && MBB.hasLabelMustBeEmitted())
3078 OutStreamer->AddComment("Label of block must be emitted");
3079 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(MBB.getSymbol());
3080 }
3081}
3082
3083void AsmPrinter::EmitBasicBlockEnd(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) {
3084 MCCodePaddingContext Context;
3085 setupCodePaddingContext(MBB, Context);
3086 OutStreamer->EmitCodePaddingBasicBlockEnd(Context);
3087}

3089void AsmPrinter::EmitVisibility(MCSymbol *Sym, unsigned Visibility,
3090 bool IsDefinition) const {
3091 MCSymbolAttr Attr = MCSA_Invalid;
3092
3093 switch (Visibility) {
3094 default: break;
3095 case GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility:
3096 if (IsDefinition)
3097 Attr = MAI->getHiddenVisibilityAttr();
3098 else
3099 Attr = MAI->getHiddenDeclarationVisibilityAttr();
3100 break;
3101 case GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility:
3102 Attr = MAI->getProtectedVisibilityAttr();
3103 break;
3104 }
3105
3106 if (Attr != MCSA_Invalid)
3107 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolAttribute(Sym, Attr);
3108}

3110/// isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthough - Return true if the basic block has
3111/// exactly one predecessor and the control transfer mechanism between
3112/// the predecessor and this block is a fall-through.
3113bool AsmPrinter::
3114isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthrough(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
3115 // If this is a landing pad, it isn't a fall through. If it has no preds,
3116 // then nothing falls through to it.
3117 if (MBB->isEHPad() || MBB->pred_empty())
3118 return false;
3119
3120 // If there isn't exactly one predecessor, it can't be a fall through.
3121 if (MBB->pred_size() > 1)
3122 return false;
3123
3124 // The predecessor has to be immediately before this block.
3125 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *MBB->pred_begin();
3126 if (!Pred->isLayoutSuccessor(MBB))
3127 return false;
3128
3129 // If the block is completely empty, then it definitely does fall through.
3130 if (Pred->empty())
3131 return true;
3132
3133 // Check the terminators in the previous blocks
3134 for (const auto &MI : Pred->terminators()) {
3135 // If it is not a simple branch, we are in a table somewhere.
3136 if (!MI.isBranch() || MI.isIndirectBranch())
3137 return false;
3138
3139 // If we are the operands of one of the branches, this is not a fall
3140 // through. Note that targets with delay slots will usually bundle
3141 // terminators with the delay slot instruction.
3142 for (ConstMIBundleOperands OP(MI); OP.isValid(); ++OP) {
3143 if (OP->isJTI())
3144 return false;
3145 if (OP->isMBB() && OP->getMBB() == MBB)
3146 return false;
3147 }
3148 }
3149
3150 return true;
3151}

3153GCMetadataPrinter *AsmPrinter::GetOrCreateGCPrinter(GCStrategy &S) {
3154 if (!S.usesMetadata())
3155 return nullptr;
3156
3157 gcp_map_type &GCMap = getGCMap(GCMetadataPrinters);
3158 gcp_map_type::iterator GCPI = GCMap.find(&S);
3159 if (GCPI != GCMap.end())
3160 return GCPI->second.get();
3161
3162 auto Name = S.getName();
3163
3164 for (GCMetadataPrinterRegistry::iterator
3165 I = GCMetadataPrinterRegistry::begin(),
3166 E = GCMetadataPrinterRegistry::end(); I != E; ++I)
3167 if (Name == I->getName()) {
3168 std::unique_ptr<GCMetadataPrinter> GMP = I->instantiate();
3169 GMP->S = &S;
3170 auto IterBool = GCMap.insert(std::make_pair(&S, std::move(GMP)));
3171 return IterBool.first->second.get();
3172 }
3173
3174 report_fatal_error("no GCMetadataPrinter registered for GC: " + Twine(Name));
3175}

3177void AsmPrinter::emitStackMaps(StackMaps &SM) {
3178 GCModuleInfo *MI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<GCModuleInfo>();
3179 assert(MI && "AsmPrinter didn't require GCModuleInfo?");
3180 bool NeedsDefault = false;
3181 if (MI->begin() == MI->end())
3182 // No GC strategy, use the default format.
3183 NeedsDefault = true;
3184 else
3185 for (auto &I : *MI) {
3186 if (GCMetadataPrinter *MP = GetOrCreateGCPrinter(*I))
3187 if (MP->emitStackMaps(SM, *this))
3188 continue;
3189 // The strategy doesn't have printer or doesn't emit custom stack maps.
3190 // Use the default format.
3191 NeedsDefault = true;
3192 }
3193
3194 if (NeedsDefault)
3195 SM.serializeToStackMapSection();
3196}

3203// In the binary's "xray_instr_map" section, an array of these function entries
3204// describes each instrumentation point. When XRay patches your code, the index
3205// into this table will be given to your handler as a patch point identifier.
3206void AsmPrinter::XRayFunctionEntry::emit(int Bytes, MCStreamer *Out,
3207 const MCSymbol *CurrentFnSym) const {
3208 Out->EmitSymbolValue(Sled, Bytes);
3209 Out->EmitSymbolValue(CurrentFnSym, Bytes);
3210 auto Kind8 = static_cast<uint8_t>(Kind);
3211 Out->EmitBinaryData(StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&Kind8), 1));
3212 Out->EmitBinaryData(
3213 StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&AlwaysInstrument), 1));
3214 Out->EmitBinaryData(StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&Version), 1));
3215 auto Padding = (4 * Bytes) - ((2 * Bytes) + 3);
3216 assert(Padding >= 0 && "Instrumentation map entry > 4 * Word Size");
3217 Out->EmitZeros(Padding);
3218}
3219
3220void AsmPrinter::emitXRayTable() {
3221 if (Sleds.empty())
3222 return;
3223
3224 auto PrevSection = OutStreamer->getCurrentSectionOnly();
3225 const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
3226 MCSection *InstMap = nullptr;
3227 MCSection *FnSledIndex = nullptr;
3228 if (MF->getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
3229 auto Associated = dyn_cast<MCSymbolELF>(CurrentFnSym);
3230 assert(Associated != nullptr);
3231 auto Flags = ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER;
3232 std::string GroupName;
3233 if (F.hasComdat()) {
3234 Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP;
3235 GroupName = F.getComdat()->getName();
3236 }
3237
3238 auto UniqueID = ++XRayFnUniqueID;
3239 InstMap =
3240 OutContext.getELFSection("xray_instr_map", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, Flags, 0,
3241 GroupName, UniqueID, Associated);
3242 FnSledIndex =
3243 OutContext.getELFSection("xray_fn_idx", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, Flags, 0,
3244 GroupName, UniqueID, Associated);
3245 } else if (MF->getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO()) {
3246 InstMap = OutContext.getMachOSection("__DATA", "xray_instr_map", 0,
3247 SectionKind::getReadOnlyWithRel());
3248 FnSledIndex = OutContext.getMachOSection("__DATA", "xray_fn_idx", 0,
3249 SectionKind::getReadOnlyWithRel());
3250 } else {
3251 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported target");
3252 }
3253
3254 auto WordSizeBytes = MAI->getCodePointerSize();
3255
3256 // Now we switch to the instrumentation map section. Because this is done
3257 // per-function, we are able to create an index entry that will represent the
3258 // range of sleds associated with a function.
3259 MCSymbol *SledsStart = OutContext.createTempSymbol("xray_sleds_start", true);
3260 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(InstMap);
3261 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(SledsStart);
3262 for (const auto &Sled : Sleds)
3263 Sled.emit(WordSizeBytes, OutStreamer.get(), CurrentFnSym);
3264 MCSymbol *SledsEnd = OutContext.createTempSymbol("xray_sleds_end", true);
3265 OutStreamer->EmitLabel(SledsEnd);
3266
3267 // We then emit a single entry in the index per function. We use the symbols
3268 // that bound the instrumentation map as the range for a specific function.
3269 // Each entry here will be 2 * word size aligned, as we're writing down two
3270 // pointers. This should work for both 32-bit and 64-bit platforms.
3271 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(FnSledIndex);
3272 OutStreamer->EmitCodeAlignment(2 * WordSizeBytes);
3273 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(SledsStart, WordSizeBytes, false);
3274 OutStreamer->EmitSymbolValue(SledsEnd, WordSizeBytes, false);
3275 OutStreamer->SwitchSection(PrevSection);
3276 Sleds.clear();
3277}

3279void AsmPrinter::recordSled(MCSymbol *Sled, const MachineInstr &MI,
3280 SledKind Kind, uint8_t Version) {
3281 const Function &F = MI.getMF()->getFunction();
3282 auto Attr = F.getFnAttribute("function-instrument");
3283 bool LogArgs = F.hasFnAttribute("xray-log-args");
3284 bool AlwaysInstrument =
3285 Attr.isStringAttribute() && Attr.getValueAsString() == "xray-always";
3286 if (Kind == SledKind::FUNCTION_ENTER && LogArgs)
3287 Kind = SledKind::LOG_ARGS_ENTER;
3288 Sleds.emplace_back(XRayFunctionEntry{Sled, CurrentFnSym, Kind,
3289 AlwaysInstrument, &F, Version});
3290}
